title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add nuts to mixture.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in a sauce pan; add brown sugar, eggs, and vanilla mix well.
Stir in flour mixture 1/2 at a time.
Spread in greased 9 by 13 inch pan; sprinkle with chocolate chips on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Strain excess liquid from cottage cheese.
Mix the cottage cheese, Feta cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper together. Butter cookie sheet.
Set oven to 350°.
Take 2 sheets of filo dough; turn up about 3-inches.
Spread cheeses on dough in one straight line across.
Turn in ends and roll up.
When cookie sheet is full, take pastry brush and lightly brush margarine on all exposed dough.
Bake until browned, about 1/2 hour.

title: can't stop snack mix
directions: Mix dressing mix and oil well.
Mix all remaining items.
Pour dressing mixture over cereal mixture.
Let stand 24 to 48 hours.

title: green lime jello
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Add sour cream, then the crushed pineapple and juice.
Put in jello mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet.
Dice onion and garlic.
Add onion, garlic, green chilies and mushrooms to meat.
Cook until all of the ingredients are done.
Drain, and set aside.

title: rolls
directions: Measure and dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Mix in 2 cups sugar, salt, oil, and egg.
Mix in flour.
Mix well.
Cover with damp cloth.
Keep in the refrigerator 2 hours before baking, shape into balls and let rise until double in size.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be kept in fridge for 2 weeks, if covered with damp cloth.

title: andrew's ants on a log
directions: Cut celery into 3-inch pieces (logs).
Spread peanut butter onto celery.
Put a row of raisins on top of filling (ants).

title: raspberry salad
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch glass dish, lightly sprayed with Pam.
In a mixing bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add cold water. Stir in berries and pecans.
Pour in dish.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: sunflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, pineapple, carrot, raisins and sunflower nuts.
Spoon yogurt over cabbage mixture and toss to coat evenly. Yields 6 servings.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Layer chicken breast and cheese in greased pan.
Pour wine and soup over chicken and cheese.
Top with 2 cups stuffing mix.
Melt butter and spread over stuffing mix.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: better than heaven cake
directions: Bake cake and then poke holes in the top with a fork.
While warm, pour Eagle Brand and caramel topping over the top.
Let cake cool.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Crumble Heath candy bars on top.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Place hot dogs in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over hot dogs.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix buttermilk and soda.
Add sugar, syrup and oleo; cook to 240°.
Remove from heat; add nuts and beat.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: hash brown casserole 2
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put into baking dish and bake for 45 minutes.

title: corn custard
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add corn, sugar, flour, butter, milk and salt.
Lastly, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in buttered pan in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.
Better results if placed in pan of water while baking.

title: corn casserole
directions: Crumble up bread and brown in skillet with a little butter and then spread on top of casserole. Bake.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Wash and shred unpeeled zucchini.
Chop onions and celery. Beat eggs.
Mix all vegetables with eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in dry cornbread mix.
Pour in skillet with about 1/2 cup heated oil or shortening.
Stir-fry.

title: mumsey's dressing
directions: Stir dry ingredients together, then stir in eggs.
Add broth and water until soft and moist.
Dip with an ice cream scoop and put balls side by side in a large, flat casserole dish or baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until nicely browned.

title: surprise baked custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt together until well blended. Gradually stir in mix.
Add vanilla.
Place one tablespoon surprise ingredients in each of 6 (6-ounce) custard cups.
Pour custard mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Set in large baking pan and pour very hot water into pan to within 1/2 inch of top of custards.
Bake at 350° until a knife inserted near center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings at 115 calories.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Boil beans and ham bone for about 3 hours or until tender. Add onion, garlic and salt.
Serve over rice.

title: nana's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown one side of meat in margarine in large heavy Dutch oven. Slice onions and garlic on top of meat while browning other side. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until boiling. Reduce heat to low and cook 4 to 5 hours, stirring frequently to prevent scorching or until sauce thickens.
Ladle over cooked spaghetti noodles.
Serve with sliced pork roast.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat oven
to
Place
bread cubes in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients;
mix.
If there is too much liquid, add more
bread
cubes.
Pour
into
a 9 x 13-inch pan and pat down evenly.
Place
pan
into
another,
larger
pan with hot water, 1-inch deep.
Bake for about 50 minutes, or until knife inserted 1 inch
from
edge
comes out clean.
Cool; cut into squares. Delicious warm or cold!

title: pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in beaten egg.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roll pork chops in dressing mix.
Pour remainder of egg over pork chops.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave taco soup
directions: Brown meat in a 3-quart casserole dish in the microwave for about 7 minutes on High.
Stir a couple of times and be sure the meat is crumbled while you are browning it.
Drain.
Add the taco seasoning mix and the Hidden Valley seasoning mix to the browned meat and stir.
Add all the other ingredients and microwave on High for about 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir about halfway through the cooking time.
Serve with grated cheese and corn chips if you desire.
This is even better the second day.

title: applesauce cake
directions: To applesauce, add soda, spices and sugar and mix well. Blend in salt
and
flour.
Beat,
then
add raisins and nuts. Stir in melted butter last.
Line a 9-inch tube pan with waxed paper and grease.
Turn
batter
into pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about
hour
and
minutes
or until done. Store cake in a cake keeper for about a week before cutting.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/4-inch pieces (remove stringy part). Combine 1 cup sugar, lemon rind, 1/2 cup Bisquick and rhubarb; toss.
Place result in 9-inch greased pan.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick, 1/4 cup butter (melted), 1 egg and 2/3 cup sugar.
Spread or dab over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes or until cake-like and medium golden brown.

title: two layer pear and cheese salad
directions: Drain pears, measuring juice.
Add water to juice to make 3/4 cup.
Dice pears, reserving a few slices for garnish, if desired. Bring measured liquid to a boil; add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
If necessary, remove unmelted ice.
Measure 1/2 cup into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill until set but not firm; add pears, cheese, salt and ginger to remaining gelatin.
Spoon over clear layer.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold.
Garnish with reserved pear slices.
Makes about 3 cups or 6 servings.
Contains 50 calories per serving.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Put in buttered baking dish. Top casserole with the black olives and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter and pumpkin soup(a thick and filling chef style soup)
directions: Toast peanuts
on
a baking sheet in a 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Hold in a warm oven.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage and 1 teaspoon sugar about 3 minutes; drain and cool.
Cut core out to loosen leaves.

title: hungarian cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage in a large pan of boiling water so you can bend the cabbage without breaking it.
In a skillet brown the onions and rice in lard slowly.
Take off stove and add meat, salt, paprika and pepper.
Mix together.
Put mixture onto leaves.
Fold over neatly, but not too tight.
Put a layer of sauerkraut in bottom of pan you are going to cook them in.
Put a layer of cabbage rolls, then a layer of kraut.
Pour tomato puree over top of rolls.
Add water up to the top of the cover.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: deep fried okra
directions: Wash and drain okra.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine flour, cracker meal, salt and pepper in shallow dish.
Combine egg, buttermilk and 1/2 teaspoon salt in bowl and beat well.
Add about 1/3 of okra at at time to milk mixture.
Remove with slotted spoon and place in flour mixture.
Coat well and drop in heated oil until brown.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thinly.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Rinse.
Add spices.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over cucumbers and freeze.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Trim the crusts from day-old bread.
Cut into cubes the size you want your croutons to be.
Place the cubes on an ungreased baking sheet and toast in a 350° oven until they are golden brown. In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of butter at a time.
When the butter's foam begins to subside, add a batch of the toasted bread cubes and saute lightly on all sides.
Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.

title: quick brunch coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in 4 tablespoons margarine; add milk, egg and vanilla.

Add 1 cup Grape-Nuts flakes; pour into 8 x 8-inch greased Corning Ware dish. Melt the other 4 tablespoons margarine; add brown sugar, remaining cereal and pecans; then sprinkle on top of coffee cake. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy bean dip
directions: Spread 1 can refried beans in a casserole dish.
Cover with cream cheese.
Add the second can of beans on top of cream cheese. Top with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove cover for the last few minutes.
Pour hot or mild sauce over the casserole before serving, or serve the sauce on the side if you prefer.

title: caramel cream pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip well for 2 minutes.
Put into pie shell.
Melt and mix together oleo and pecans in a saucepan to coat nuts.
Spread over top of pie. Drizzle caramel sauce over top.
Cover with foil.
Freeze.
Thaw slightly just to ease slicing stage.
Serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes very thin.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch roasting pan. Slice onion thin and place over potatoes; salt and pepper. Sprinkle with flour.
Cover with milk.
Brown pork chops and lay on top.
Turn pork chops at least once while baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: four layered delight
directions: Mix together; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: the old pallie
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add milk, eggs and dry ingredients.
Bake in stem pan at 350°.
Ice with any icing or good served just plain.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon and cheese in pie shell.
Beat eggs until blended.
Mix with cream and milk.
Pour over cheese and bacon. Sprinkle nutmeg over filling.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon cookie bars
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix into flour. Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into a log about 14 inches by 1 1/2 inches.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Make a depression down center of each log about 1/2-inch wide.
Spoon in pie filling, mounding slightly.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tops are set and bottoms are golden.
Let cool 2 minutes and loosen bottoms with spatula.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool completely before cutting into 1-inch slices.

title: valentine punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until a thin syrup forms.
Add juices. Chill.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: boneless chicken breast
directions: Place flour and pepper in bag and shake.
Place chicken in bag and shake until coated.
Heat oil in pan and saute chicken 10 minutes per side until golden brown.
Remove chicken.
Saute onion, mushrooms and lemon juice for 5 minutes.
Add white wine and return chicken to pan.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes over low heat.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour.
Mix and form into balls.
Roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken-cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Just before serving, shred lettuce with knife (about 4 cups). In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Add vinegar; heat through.
Remove skillet from heat; add lettuce and onions. Season with salt, pepper and sugar; toss 1 to 2 minutes until lettuce is wilted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yellow squash pie
directions: Mix all together well and put in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Mix the next 3 ingredients good and pour over the first mixture.
Mix the pudding and milk and pour over the second part.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients in large bowl.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Defrost potatoes before mixing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a large 9 x 13 x 2-inch or 2 (2-quart) casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pat's garlicky onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large Dutch oven or soup pot over medium heat. Add olive oil.
Coarsely chop onions, add gradually to butter, stirring frequently.
When all onions are in pot, add chopped garlic.
Cook until all onions are clear.
Add wine, thyme, and oregano and simmer for 20-30 minutes, until reduced by about 1/3. Add beef broth and roasted garlic.
Simmer 20-30 minutes to mix flavors.
Ladle into heavy oven proof bowls.
Place a slice of good bread and Provolone cheese on top, place in 250 degree oven for about 5 minutes to melt cheese.

title: shrimp in aspic
directions: Heat tomato juice; add vinegar, salt, horseradish and onion. Simmer for a few minutes.
Add dry Jell-O and mix well.
Add shrimp.
Pour into mold and chill.
Remove from mold and fill center with mayonnaise.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued meats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and cut meat in 2-inch cubes. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange walnut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Add orange juice, egg, butter and orange peel.
Stir until moist.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into 8 x 4-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: overnight cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a greased Bundt pan, place half the frozen dough balls, powdered pudding mix, brown sugar, cinnamon, butter and pecans. Repeat with remaining amounts.
Cover the pan loosely with foil, sprayed with Pam on the side next to the pan.
Then cover with a clean towel.
Allow to sit on counter overnight.
It will rise overnight.
If risen over top of pan, punch with fingers and it will fall back.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries, orange (cut up), peeling too, and 1 cup water in blender and put on chop.
Fix the jello with the 2 cups of hot water, stir in the sugar.
Mix with the cranberries and nuts. Chill.

title: kitchen crew hamburger pie
directions: Stir 1 cup Bisquick and the milk into a soft dough.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured board.
Knead.
Roll dough to make a pie crust.
Ease into pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion.
Stir in salt and pepper, 2 tablespoons Bisquick and Worcestershire.
Spoon into pie crust.
Beat eggs slightly; mix with cheese.
Pour over meat mixture.
Cover edge with 2 to 3 inch strip of foil to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil last 5 minutes of baking.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut into wedges. Serve with chili sauce.

title: butternut marshmallows
directions: Chop walnuts fine.
Firmly pack brown sugar before measuring. Mix together sugar, cream, vanilla and salt.
Place over heat and slowly bring mixture to a boil, gently, until candy thermometer registers 238° or until a little candy dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Drop in marshmallows, a few at a time, and turn with a fork until well coated.
Remove and roll in chopped nuts.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Cook frozen broccoli a couple of minutes in boiling water.
Warm Cheez Whiz in microwave and add to cream soup.
Layer 1/2 rice, all broccoli, 1/2 soup and cheese mix, onion rings, rest of rice and rest of soup and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours, the longer it is refrigerated, the better it will set.
Cheese cake can then be topped with the pie filling of your choice.

title: noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out into thin sheet; let dry. Roll like jelly roll and slice thin.
Shake out.
Drop into boiling beef or chicken broth.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown on top.
Makes its own crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sourdough starter with yeast
directions: Pour warm water in a 2 qt. container (crock, glass, or plastic).
Sprinkle yeast over water, stirring until dissolved. Beat in the flour and sugar with a wire whisk until smooth.
Cover container with cheesecloth.
Place in protected spot and leave until sponge begins to bubble, rises, and falls back.
Stir with rubber spatula, replace cheesecloth and allow to bubble about 2 days.
Stir thoroughly, label, place lid over cheesecloth and refrigerate.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° 30 to 35 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, milk and butter; bring to a boil and boil 3 1/2 minutes.
Take off heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper with teaspoon.

title: pineapple coconut pies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended and smooth. Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Serve with assorted fruits, cookies or cake cubes.
Makes 2 cups (approximately 6 calories per teaspoon).

title: belynda's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Grate or finely chop 1/2 package of the chocolate.
Set aside. Heat remaining chocolate and milk in pan over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Whisk in cream cheese until smooth.
Cool 5 minutes.
Fold in 3 1/2 cups Cool Whip and the grated chocolate. Spread in pie shell.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Soak potatoes in water for 10 minutes; drain and squeeze dry in kitchen towel.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except the oil; mix thoroughly.
Pour oil in large skillet (1/8-inch deep).
Place over medium heat.
For each pancake, pour 1/2 cup potato mixture into the pan; flatten slightly.
Cook about 8 minutes, until crispy and brown, turning once.
Repeat with more oil and potato mixture.
Serve with sour cream and applesauce, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Crush together and place in bottom and sides of 11 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan or 3 pie pans (9-inch).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Spread rolls in bottom of a 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top rolls with sausage and cheese.
Heat eggs, milk and salt, but do not boil.
Stir with a wire whisk while heating.
Pour over sausage mixture in casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator about 30 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Mold into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Chill a couple of hours.
Roll in nuts when ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: jailhouse chili
directions: Brown cubed steak.
Add ground steak.
Saute onions and garlic.
Add tomato paste and water.
Add cayenne, cumin and jalapeno pepper, then simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hour.
Add dark kidney beans, if preferred.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes more.

title: party eggnog
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix in syrup, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in orange juice and lemon juice.
Cut ice cream into chunks the size of small eggs.
Put into large punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over ice cream.
Stir in egg mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: fruit parfait
directions: Whip skim milk with hand and blend until thick (yogurt texture), then add fruit.
Blend until fruit is mixed.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix tuna and soup in saucepan; heat until warm.
Put mixture on buns.
Put cheese on mixture and top off with top bun.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with chips. Makes 6 servings.

title: oven-barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs in a single layer in large baking pans. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings. Turn ribs. Bake 30 minutes longer. Meanwhile, in a saucepan, saute onions and celery in reserved drippings until tender. Stir in a remaining ingredients; bring to a boil drain ribs; pour sauce over ribs. Cover and bake for 15 minutes; turn ribs and baste. Bake 15 minutes longer or until tender. Yield: 12 servings.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and oregano.
Season
chicken
with
garlic powder and Season-All. Roll
in oleo, then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Preheat oven to 450° in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange broccoli and chicken in small bowl.
Combine soup and milk; pour over broccoli and chicken. Combine bread crumbs, margarine or butter.
Sprinkle over top. Bake 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix together all other ingredients, except for 1/2 cup of cheese.
Add spaghetti and carefully mix together.
Put in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top during the last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5 to 6.
This casserole may be made the day before.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in 5 cups boiling water until thick.
Brown sausage with onion and set aside.
Add to grits the margarine, eggs, sausage and onion.
Stir until margarine melts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9 x 9-inch) pans and freeze one.
Sprinkle with parsley, paprika and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: single crust
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Combine flour and salt in a mixing bowl.

With a pastry blender or two knives, cut in shortening until uniform; mixture should be fairly coarse. Sprinkle with water, a tablespoon at a time; toss with a fork. Work dough into a firm ball with your hands.
Roll under to make a double thickness of dough into pie pan.
Fold under to make double thickness of dough around rim and flute with fingers or fork. Prick crust with fork and bake in
preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes or lightly brown.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix together sweetened condensed milk, coconut and flavorings. Drop by tablespoonfuls, about 1-inch apart onto a well-greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned around the edges.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.

title: country fried round steak
directions: Cut round steak into six serving pieces.
Pound steak on both sides thoroughly.
Blend egg and milk.
Dip pieces of meat first in egg, then in crumbs.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Layer in 2 1/2-quart casserole: Line bottom and sides with corn tortillas, then ground meat mixture, 1 can Ranch Style beans, slices of Velveeta cheese, corn tortillas, 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll onto well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour melted chocolate chips over top.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch slices.
Leave in pan and chill for 2 to 3 hours. Serve cold.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: For each cookie, arrange 1 graham cracker in center of paper napkin or paper towel; top with chocolate and marshmallow.
Cover with graham cracker and wrap in napkin.
Arrange on glass oven tray.
Heat at High for 3/4 to 1 minute.
Let stand 2 minutes before unwrapping.
Makes 4 cookies.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Generously grease 4 (12-cup) muffin tins; set aside.
Place butter, sugar and salt in a very large mixing bowl.
Scald milk. Pour over butter, sugar and salt.
Cool until warm to fingertips. Add beaten egg yolks and yeast.
Mix well.
Start adding flour, 3 to 4 cups at a time, beating well after each addition until dough is slightly stiff.
Place dough on floured surface and knead, adding more flour if necessary.
Return dough to mixing bowl and grease with butter.
Cover and let rise double in bulk.
Punch dough down (I let mine rise twice).
Shape into balls, placing two in each muffin tin cup.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Grease tops with butter.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil water and dissolve sugar and Jell-O.
Mix all ingredients in a gallon jug.
Fill with water and shake.
Freeze.
Let thaw 12 hours before serving.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Make pudding as directed.
Mix with the Cool Whip.

title: herring salad(a swedish classic)
directions: Drain herring pieces and cut into dices.
Discard remaining sauce in jar.
Mix thoroughly, but carefully, the herring, potatoes, beets, gherkin, apple and onions.

Blend vinegar, water, sugar and pepper well and add to mixture, stirring gently. (Dyed-in-the-wool Swedes fold in a 1/2 cup stiffly-whipped cream at this stage, but it is not necessary; the dish is delicious without it.)
Pack mix in chilled mold and refrigerate overnight. Unmold and garnish with sliced eggs.
Serve with sour cream beaten stiff and colored with pickled beet juice.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup mixture for topping.
Press rest into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.

title: hickory nut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add sugar, nuts and vanilla. Drop from teaspoon on greased pan. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Soak cracklins in warm water and let them get soft (about 5 minutes).
Mash them in the water to get them into smaller pieces. Add cornmeal and salt (if too sticky, add more meal).
Put in greased pie pan and cook at 350° until brown.

title: pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in bottom of casserole dish. Top with sliced pepper and onion.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ruth's chicken and dressing scallop
directions: Prepare bread stuffing as directed on package; let cool. Simmer chicken, bouillon cube, soup and seasonings until chicken is cooked.
In pan, mix flour, butter and 4 cups broth (from chicken).
Cook until thick.
Add 6 beaten eggs to gravy.
Liquid is hot, so add a small portion to eggs, then the balance.
(If prepared in advance, the eggs can be added to the cooled mixture of gravy.)
Place dressing in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with chicken.
Pour gravy over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peppery dip with vegetables
directions: Several hours before serving:
In a small bowl, with spoon stir all ingredients except vegetables; cover and refrigerate.

title: ham and onion rolls
directions: Cut cream cheese into 8 pieces.
Pat dry ham slices and spread cream cheese on ham.
Roll up around an onion, refrigerate over night.
Slice into small pieces.

title: date nut rocks
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla, soda (dissolved in 1 tablespoon water) and eggs.
Combine flour, dates, nuts, cinnamon and allspice.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture and drop onto a lightly greased cookie sheet a teaspoonful at a time.
Place fairly far apart as they spread quite a lot.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: texas pea salad
directions: Break lettuce in bite size.
Spread in glass dish.
Spread celery over lettuce.
Sprinkle onions over celery.
Put peas over onions.
Add sugar to Miracle Whip and spread over peas.
Spread bacon bits over Miracle Whip.
Spread shredded cheese over all. Could use boiled eggs for a layer.

title: best ever quiche
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Flake ham by pressing sides with fork.
Place broccoli, ham, cheese and onion in unbaked pie crust.
Pour liquid mixture over ingredients in pie crust.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add other ingredients.
Spread in square, greased pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Bake in slow oven.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta with vegetables; drain.
Toss with oil.
Add Parmesan cheese.

title: beat and eat cake frosting
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in small, deep bowl.
Add boiling water and beat until stiff.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add 2 to 3 peeled and cut up ripe tomatoes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line casserole with Doritos.
Combine all other ingredients, except cheese and pour over Doritos.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: yummies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° until brown.
May be frosted.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring to a boil the onion, tomato soup, sugar, oil, green pepper, vinegar, dry mustard, salt and pepper and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: potato and chipped beef casserole
directions: Heat chipped beef and frizzle in butter; add soup and milk. Mix well with diced, skinned potatoes.
Mix well; season with pepper, onion, mustard and cheese (optional).
Pour into casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine last 3 ingredients in medium bowl; mix until well blended. Gradually add dry mixture until just blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Sometimes I make cupcakes; baking time is less.
Test with toothpick or knife.)
Can be iced with buttercream icing; orange-flavored is my favorite.

title: deridder casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef with green pepper and onion until the meat is browned and the vegetables are tender; drain.
Add next 11 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add noodles and mix well.

title: orange julia
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until there are no longer large ice chunks.
Pour and serve.

title: potato gnocchi
directions: Steam the potatoes in their skins until tender.
When they are cool, peel and mash.
Immediately add the flour and salt.
Knead on a lightly floured board until smooth.
Sprinkle on a little more flour if the dough sticks.
Form into rolls about the thickness of your thumb.
Cut into 3/4-inch sections and press down lightly with fork.
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Add the gnocchi and boil until they rise to the top.
Make in small batches.
Drain and place in warm bowl.
Add sauce to coat.

title: quick-cool salad
directions: Mix 4 ingredients together and presto - a great salad.

title: exotic luncheon salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise with soy sauce and curry powder.
Add to bowl and toss lightly.
Chill several hours and serve over lettuce.
Serves 12.

title: marinated pork strips(32 strips)
directions: Trim the fat from the tenderloins.
If thick, split lengthwise.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except the oil, in a bowl.
Marinate the pork in the mixture three hours in the refrigerator, turning and basting frequently.
Drain and reserve the marinade.
Preheat oven to moderate (375°).
Transfer the pork to an oiled roasting pan and roast until tender, about forty-five minutes.
Simmer the marinade ten minutes.
Cut the pork into thin slices and serve on cocktail picks with the marinade as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: marshmallow jewel pie
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until marshmallows are melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Soften gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Add softened gelatin, salt and vanilla to marshmallow mixture.
Mix well.
Chill until partially set, 30 to 60 minutes.
Beat chilled marshmallow mixture with electric mixer (medium speed) until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream and fruit cocktail.
Put in crust.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted water as instructed on the package. Drain and rinse under cold water.
Pour one tablespoon salad oil over noodles and toss to coat with oil to prevent sticking together.
Saute onions and peppers in 3 tablespoons oil or margarine.
Add diced, cooked chicken, soup, milk and diced pimento.
Cook over medium heat until blended and smooth.

title: rocky road cookies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of chocolate chips and the butter over low heat; cool.
Heat oven to 400°.

Mix remaining chips, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, nuts and chocolate mixture. Drop dough by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Press a marshmallow in center of each.
Bake 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350 degrees 30 - 40 minutes.

title: crisp baked fish filets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°. Wash and dry filets and cut into serving pieces. Dip in oil and coat with cornflake crumbs. Arrange in single layer in a lightly oiled shallow baking dish so that the pieces do not touch each other. Season. Bake 10 minutes without turning or basting. Serves 4.

title: sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine margarine, sweetener, vanilla and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally until well combined.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and water. Beat at low speed until well combined (about 2 minutes).
Stir in rolled oats (dough will be soft).
Drop by rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 42 cookies.

title: old-fashioned raisin filled cookies
directions: Cook raisins, sugar and water 8 minutes or until thick. Remove from heat; add lemon juice and butter.
Let cool.

title: greasy rice
directions: Saute rice in butter over low heat until rice turns golden (about 10 minutes).
Add 2 or 3 cans chicken broth.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add cereal and then add liquids.
Mix together until well blended.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on a 12-inch service plate.
In small bowl mash avocado, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread over bean dip. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; spread over avocado layer.
Sprinkle with cheese, olives, onions and tomato. Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: quick homemade chili
directions: Brown the hamburger meat and diced onion in a skillet.
Drain. In large saucepan, add meat and onion with other ingredients. May add hot sauce, if desired.
Cook on medium-high for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Heat soup and cheese until cheese melts.
Cool completely. Add mayonnaise and chopped vegetables.
Add gelatine, softened with 2 tablespoons water.
Makes enough for 3 small bowls.
Good served with vegetable sticks or chips.

title: orange creme dessert with ruby cranberry sauce(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 9-inch spring-form pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Press cookie crumbs into bottom of spray-coated spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Chill in refrigerator or freezer.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil together the sugar, margarine and milk.
Mix together oatmeal, coconut, cocoa and salt in a bowl.
Pour syrup over oatmeal mixture.
Stir until thick.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Set until firm.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift together flour and soda.
Cream shortening thoroughly. Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Alternate dry ingredients and milk.
Fold in bananas.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: south pacific bake
directions: Melt margarine in large frypan.
Flour chicken pieces and saute until golden brown on all sides.
Remove from pan and place in casserole dish.
Pour juice from oranges over top of chicken and add pineapple.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add snow peas and cover.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove cover and add oranges and pepper.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix hot water and oatmeal together and set aside.
Sift all dry ingredients together and make a well in the center.
To the well, add eggs, oil and oatmeal mixture and blend thoroughly. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: tangy broccoli-potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender (10 minutes); drain.
Steam or microwave broccoli until tender.

title: spicy crab puffs
directions: Combine first nine ingredients and mix well.
Add egg yolks and chill well.
Form into balls.
Fry in 375° oil until golden. Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter. Divide in half and put in a 9 x 13 pan. If you need more in bottom of pan,
1 cup is enough for topping.

title: carol's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into slices.
Also, onions and peppers.
Bring everything to a boil for 10 minutes.
Place right into jars and seal.
Turn jars upside-down to seal.

title: taco spread
directions: Spread the bean dip onto platter.
Mix avocados with mayo and lemon juice.
Put on top of bean dip.
Blend sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Put on top of avocado mixture.
Layer diced green onions next.
Layer tomatoes, then layer black olives next.
Top with a layer of grated Cheddar cheese.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Combine soup, chicken, 1/2 cup cheese and jalapeno pepper.
Top half of each tortilla with 1/4 cup soup mixture, spreading to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Moisten edges of tortillas with water; fold over, pressing edges to seal.
On large baking sheets, arrange filled tortillas.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef.
In saucepan, mix and heat canned sauces and soups; add meat mixture.

title: marbled chocolate bars
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch pan.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix together; spread on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: frenchman's stew
directions: Saute meat in olive oil to a golden brown; sprinkle flour over top of meat.
Chop onion, garlic and bell pepper very fine.
Add other seasonings with 1/2 cup of water.
Place lid on stew pan and simmer 2 hours.
Serves 4.
Add package of mixed vegetables, if desired.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine last 8
ingredients well.
Pour over tomatoes, cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: butter brickle bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend together on medium beater setting until thoroughly mixed together.
Pour the mixture evenly into 5 small 2 1/2 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool and remove from pans.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add soups and mushrooms.
Put in 3-quart casserole.
Top with mashed potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until potatoes are light brown and crusty.
(Other vegetables may be added.)

title: lobster diablo
directions: Mix wine, mushrooms and green pepper together and add to chopped lobster meat (baked or boiled) in a saucepan and stir constantly for 15 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in paprika and pimiento.
Add salt and pepper as desired. Transfer to a baking dish and top with a mixture of bread crumbs and cheese; bake in a moderately hot oven for 15 minutes.

title: potato-sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix soup, milk, onion, salt, pepper and cheese in a large casserole dish.
Layer potatoes, soup mixture and sausage and repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: nuts 'n berries dressing
directions: Combine cornbread, bread cubes, nuts and poultry seasoning. Stir in cranberry sauce, butter and egg; toss lightly.
Bake in 3-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts dressing.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast with 1/4 cup warm water and sugar.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.
Mix with yeast; let rise 2 hours.

title: italian dish
directions: Cook celery and onion in small amount of oil until brown.
Add meat; cook until brown.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf and oregano; stir.
Add tomatoes and paste; mix well and set aside.
Cook noodles; drain.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt chocolate bark slowly.
Spread peanut butter on Ritz crackers and sandwich the crackers with the peanut butter.
Dip each sandwich cracker in melted chocolate, using a spoon to cover the cracker.
Place on wax paper, then place in refrigerator for 30 minutes or until hard.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: In 1 inch boiling water, heat potatoes and cabbage to boiling. Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 20 minutes, or until tender.
Drain.

title: polish potato kugel
directions: Grate potatoes; put in colander.
Save starch and pour water out.
Fry salt pork and margarine.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl; mix until blended.
Grease pan; pour in ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake slowly in uncooked pie shell until done.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: homemade muffin mix
directions: In large bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Store up to 6 weeks at room temperature or up to 6 months in freezer.
Allow to come to room temperature before using, if frozen.
Makes about 14 cups mix.

title: peanut butter, oatmeal, chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes about 8 dozen medium size cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and onion. Form into balls and roll in pecan chips.
Makes 2 balls.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in salt water until tender.
Drain all of water, except small amount.
Add milk and margarine.
Then add chopped hard-boiled eggs.
Cook on low until margarine melts.
Add pepper to taste.

title: creamy icing
directions: Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together butter, sugar, Crisco and vanilla.
When first mixture is cool, combine with creamed mixture and beat with mixer until it is the consistency you desire for easy spreading.

title: crowd size chop suey
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Saute onion and pepper.
Add ground beef until done.
Add spaghetti sauce and hamburger mixture to macaroni.
Serves 125 people

title: nantucket pie
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and spread berries on bottom.
Sprinkle with sugar and nuts; set aside.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Spread filling over a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Sprinkle over filling.
Blend oil, eggs, vanilla and 1/2 cup nuts; pour over ingredients in the pan.
Stir with a fork until blended.
Smooth evenly in pan.
Bake at 500° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: travelin cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into cupcake paper-lined muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle nuts in a 9-inch pie shell. Bake until firm, about 1 hour, at 350°.
(Copied.)

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 10 minutes or until heated.

title: best brownies(in honor of l. e. c.)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Grease and flour two 8-inch or 9-inch layer pans.
Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and nutmeg.
Add blackberries to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes until done.

title: heavenly pudding
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice, stir until thick.
Add marshmallows, cherries (cut into quarters) and pineapple.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Line bowl with slices of cake or lady fingers. Pour milk mixture in.
Chill well.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Stir well with a wooden spoon. Pour into 3 small or 2 large loaf pans. Batter will be very thick. Sprinkle sugar on top. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or longer.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: raspberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello and boiling water; stir to dissolve.
Add applesauce and partially thawed berries.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together and boil 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Then add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Bake in greased square pan 30 to 40 minutes.
Glaze if desired.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Line muffin tins with foil baking cups.
Place a vanilla wafer at the bottom of each cup.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and place filling on top.
Makes 12 to 14 cupcakes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat the lemon juice.
Beat eggs and lemon rind together.
Add the milk and mix.
Combine the sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add the butter and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until custard is set.
Test by inserting silver knife in center.
When it comes out clean, the filling is set.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in pot.
Boil exactly one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and continue to stir until mixture loses its shine.
Drop teaspoonfuls on wax paper and allow to harden.

title: chicken lo mein
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Heat 1/4 cup oil in nonstick skillet.
Add 1/2 linguine and salt; cook until lightly browned, turning occasionally.
Remove and cook remaining linguine.

title: cart drivers
directions: Marinate first 5 ingredients for 1 hour.
Add macaroni. Serve warm or chilled.

title: honey mustard chicken whip-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread on chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill paper baking cups in muffin tins 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar. Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Drop 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake according to cake package directions.
Makes about 30.

title: jane's cranberry pie
directions: Cut 1/2 cup of butter or margarine into 1 cup of flour as in pie crust.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of cold water.
Mix with fork, shape into ball.
Roll or pat out into two 12 x 3-inch strips, leaving 3 inches between strips (or leave in one piece). Pastry should be about 1/4-inch thick.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Cut olives, bell pepper, onions and tomatoes in small pieces.

title: bean sprout salad
directions: Combine onions, garlic, sesame seed, sweet pepper and soy sauce.
Pour over bean sprouts.
Combine vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Add to bean sprout mixture.
Mix and chill.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all gently.
Garnish with egg slices; sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well and beat about 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured sheet cake pan for about 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: stove top barbecue beans
directions: Place strip of bacon in medium saucepan.
Heat until bacon begins to cook.
Add drained beans and other ingredients in order given; stir.
Beans are done when bacon and onion flakes are tender.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Beat together cream cheese, milk and instant pudding.
Spread mixture over cooled cake.
Sprinkle pineapple over top, then coconut.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: easy butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet; stir in sugar. Add almonds and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is golden and almonds begin to pop. Spread evenly in a jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2). Immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips. Spread.
When chocolate is set and cool, crack candy into pieces.

title: breakfast ahead
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, cook sausage and drain.
Spoon over muffins.
Beat
eggs, add sour cream and pour over sausage and muffins.
Sprinkle	cheese over top;
dot with chilies.
Cover and keep in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, put it in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
It's very good!

title: orange kiss-me cake
directions: Squeeze 1 orange. Grind together pulp and rind of orange, seedless raisins and walnuts. In mixing bowl sift together flour, soda and sugar. Add shortening and milk. Beat for 1 1/2 minutes. Fold orange-raisin-walnut mixture into batter. Mix well. Pour into 12x8x2 or 13x9x2 pan which has been well greased and lightly floured. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Drip orange juice over warm cake. Sprinkle with 1/3 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup chopped walnuts.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs until light and thick.
Add flour, salt and 1/3 cup of milk.
Keep beating until all flour is moistened.
Gradually add remaining milk and melted shortening; beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Fill greased muffin tins a little less than half full.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Beat eggs and add spinach, melted butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Fold in cottage cheese and cubed cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Prepare sauce in medium bowl.
Sprinkle dry milk over water. Beat until just blended.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and bouillon.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk.
Place over medium heat; stir constantly until thickened.
Add mushrooms.
Remove from heat.
On underneath side of each breast, place 1 or 2 slices cheese and 1 slice ham. Spoon 1 tablespoon of sauce over ham.
Fold and secure together. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of sauce over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Heat the remaining sauce and serve.

title: hawaiian cheese dip
directions: Hollow out center of loaf of bread.
Place on sheet of foil or cookie sheet.
Mix ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into center of bread.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cut remaining bread into large cubes to dip into cheese mixture.

title: giant krispie squares
directions: In large pan (Dutch oven) sprayed with vegetable spray, melt butter and add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat. Add cereal, stir until well coated.
Spread into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Use buttered wax paper to spread evenly.
Cool.
Cut into 24 (2 x 2-inch) squares.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil together until well blended.
Fold in zucchini mixture until blended.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Add nuts or coconut, if desired.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Shake biscuits in a bag with granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuits in greased tube pan. Sprinkle nuts between layers.

title: chicken spanish rice
directions: Place all ingredients in crock pot and add 1/2 cup of water, cover and cook on low heat for about 8 hours or until dinnertime.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, cornmeal, vanilla, butter and vinegar. Mix well.
Let set 10 minutes; then stir gently.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese together. Add drained pineapple and mix well. Add Cool Whip and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix together all ingredients adding paprika to make a light pink color and lemon juice to taste.
Chill for 4 1/2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Peel and slice turnips; cook with onion in boiling water until tender.
Drain off all water; salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar, 1/2 stick butter, flour and milk; mash until smooth.
Beat in egg yolks.
Beat egg white until stiff; fold into turnip mixture.
Place into well buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and 2/3 cup melted butter; spread over turnip mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes until crumbs are lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Place in casserole; top with cheese and onion rings.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix well, reserving 1/2 cup cheese for top of bread. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack into jars.
Add one head of dill, alum and 1 clove garlic to each jar.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cover with canning lids and seal. Process for only 10 minutes.
Let pickle for at least 2 weeks.

title: glorified pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together cornstarch, sugar, ginger and cinnamon.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks and cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Add pumpkin and salt; let cool.
Fold in whipped cream and beaten egg whites.
Pour into tray and freeze, stirring twice during the first half hour.

title: okra with dried apricots
directions: Scrape, dice and boil carrots in salted water until crisply done.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
In small bowl, mix carrot liquid, onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots. Top with bread crumbs and pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes or until slightly brown and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: shake pickles
directions: Place sliced cucumbers and onions in a wide mouth quart jar. Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Place a tight lid on jar.
Place jar in refrigerator. Shake jar once a day for 6 days.
These can be served after 6 days. These will keep a long time.

title: scalloped chicken and spaghetti
directions: Saute butter, onion and garlic.
Add flour and chicken stock; simmer until thickens.
Add cheese, tomatoes and chicken; cook until thick.
Pour over spaghetti or mix with spaghetti.

title: "mud" chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients in oblong pan.
Make 3 holes.
In hole #1, Wesson oil; hole #2, vinegar and hole #3, vanilla.
Pour 1 1/2 cups cold water over all.
Stir until smooth.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cooked in center, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: In large skillet, stirring frequently, brown beef, onion and garlic on medium-high heat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water. Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir about 1 cup of the sauce into mostaccioli.
Spoon 1/2 of the mostaccioli mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick strawberry bread
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and Jello. Stir until evenly mixed and make a well in center of dry ingredients.

In food processor or blender combine eggs, strawberries, banana, and oil. Blend until smooth and creamy. Pour into dry ingredients, stir by hand until dry ingredients are moistened. Grease two 9x5 loaf pans. Put equal amounts in each pan and bake on center rack of oven 45-50 min. Let cool before slicing.

title: rhubarb sour cream squares
directions: Mix sugar, nuts, margarine and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Alternate dry ingredients with sour cream and add rhubarb; turn into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping of sugar, nuts, margarine and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt
the butter in an 8 inch square pan.
Spread the graham cracker crumbs on bottom of pan.
Spread the coconut next.
Add the coconut, then the chocolate chips.
Next, add the pecans. Pour the milk over the top. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: spareribs chinese-style
directions: Bake ribs in oven
until
fat runs out, about 1 hour at 350°. Combine remaining
ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over ribs and cook 1 1/2 hours more.	Keep basting until there is no more sauce.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Let pastry sit at room temperature for 20 minutes to defrost. Roll out with flour to 14 to 15 inches.
Cut each sheet into 6 rectangles.
Spread mustard on each portion.
Place a slice of ham and cheese on each.
Roll up into logs, wetting edges to keep together.
Let sit in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, adding no seasonings.
While rice is still hot, add Cheez Whiz and soup; set aside.
Cook frozen broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and set aside, while browning the chopped onion, celery and green pepper.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Gently mix together; pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Combine sugar and syrup or honey in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently until mixture boils. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well blended, then add chocolate chips and mix well again.
The chips will soften and mix in.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares or bars (2 x 1-inch).

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of margarine, melted. Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream eggs, rest of margarine (melted), powdered sugar and vanilla, then beat with mixer for 15 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Layer sliced bananas, then pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans over Cool Whip and place cherries in rolls on cake.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add apples, vanilla, eggs and oil.
Blend together well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan and sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: the best quiche
directions: Spread pie crust with butter or margarine.
In 12-inch skillet over medium low heat, cook bacon slices.
Drain on paper towels. While still warm, roll 6 slices, one at a time, to form "roses". Keep warm.
Crumble remaining slices, sprinkle with cheese on pie crust.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Start at 300° and then increase to 325°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool, then ice the cake.

title: blueberry fluff
directions: Mix together and chill for 2 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bone.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: jimmy's secret recipe(barbecue sauce)
directions: Saute chopped onions in butter to soften.
Add all other ingredients and cook about 15 minutes.
Then add 1/2 cup Pepsi-Cola (secret ingredient - don't tell).
Boil chicken until almost done, saving broth to make rice.
Add chicken to sauce and simmer.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Break lettuce in bowl.
Add pineapple and mayonnaise.

title: mediterranean salad
directions: Toss first four ingredients together.
Combine vinegar and seasonings, then slowly whisk in olive oil and add dressing to salad mixture.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll
bread
into
1-inch
balls.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Place balls of dough in pan; alternate. Put butterscotch pudding, brown
sugar
and
cinnamon
in a bowl and mix well. Sprinkle over balls of dough. Pour melted margarine over dough and
let
settle overnight. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mexican chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In skillet, cook onion, sweet chili pepper and garlic until tender.
Then put all the ingredients into a large pot and cook slowly, about 1 hour.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Take cooking apples, peel and cut into chunks (about the size of a prune or smaller). Wrap biscuit layer around each piece of apple.
Place biscuit layers in melted margarine.
If there is some apples left over, cut in small pieces and spread around on top of other layers of apples.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Combine and bring to boil.
Pour over sliced cucumbers and let stand for 2 more days.
On third day, put cucumbers and syrup on stove and bring to boil.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: easy taters
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into wedges.
Mix next 4 ingredients together in a plastic bag and coat potatoes completely.
Melt margarine in large pan (9 x 13-inch).
Dip potatoes in melted margarine and place in pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake another 20 minutes.
Serve with baked beans and fried chicken.

title: wine soup(vinesuppe)
directions: Soak separately overnight the tapioca and prunes.
Cook the prunes in one quart of water until tender.
Add the tapioca and the rest of the ingredients and cook slowly until the tapioca is dissolved.
Add the lemon at the end of the cooking time.

title: carol chaves' jello recipe
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Mix lemon Jell-O in 1 cup hot water, let cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add Jell-O and whipping cream, whipped (use real whipping cream).
Pour on top of crust.
Mix remaining Jell-O and 3 cups hot water.
After lemon gel is hardened and this mix is cooled, pour on top of lemon Jell-O mix.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix together.
Let sit several hours or overnight in refrigerator to blend flavors.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil margarine, cocoa and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour and spread over cake while hot.

title: easy vegetables
directions: Spray casserole dish with cooking spray.
Peel and slice potatoes and carrots.
Arrange in a casserole dish.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and butter.
Pour in 1/4 cup milk.
Bake until potatoes are tender.
Fix broccoli and cheese according to directions.
Pour over potatoes and carrots.
Serve.

title: carrot salad
directions: Finely chop carrots.
Mix all ingredients well.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: party punch
directions: Spoon sherbet into a large punch bowl. Add lemonade concentrate and 1 1/2 cups cold water. Stir just until combined. Slowly pour Sprite down the side of the bowl; stir gently to mix. Makes 32 (4 ounce) servings.

title: pumpkin spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add sugar or spices to taste. Serve on pumpkin breads or serve with gingersnap cookies as a dip.

title: old timer spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350°.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Blend all ingredients, except corn, cheese and chilies, about 20 seconds. Beat vigorously 1 minute. Fold in corn, cheese and chilies. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender (approximately 10 minutes). Place in greased casserole. Saute onion and celery in melted margarine until tender, 5 to 10 minutes. Stir in soup, Cheez Whiz and rice. Mix well. Add to broccoli in casserole (2 quart). Mix well. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Bake in preheated oven at 350 degree oven (covered) for approximately 30-40 minutes.

title: sponge candy
directions: Cook to 300° hard crack the first 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat and add the baking powder.
Stir very quickly and pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
This will harden very fast.
Break into pieces.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Spoon mixture over chicken and bake for 45 minutes at 375°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: vanilla pudding(lo-cal)
directions: Put crumbled crackers in square dish. Mix up pudding according to directions.
Layer pudding on top of crackers; alternate with bananas.
Top with Cool Whip (optional).
Easy and low calorie.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine rest of ingredients except sauce and cheese.
Pour into 2 round pizza pans.
Sprinkle on hamburger.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.
Take out and top with sauce and cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix bread, meat, milk, salt, and onions well.
Form balls and fry until browned.
Combine vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, and ketchup.
Pour sauce over meatballs and simmer for 1/2 hour. Just before serving, spear each meatball with a pretzel (stick) so your guests can easily pick them up!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil; add beans, artichoke, breadcrumbs and cheese.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Take out yolks and mix with the other ingredients, then stuff the eggs with the mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: zippy corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add broth and potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes until potatoes are almost tender.
Stir in jalapeno, mustard, salt, paprika and red pepper flakes.
Add corn, green onions and 2 1/2 c milk.
Bring to a boil.
Combine flour and remaining milk until smooth, and gradually add to soup.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry-oatmeal cookies
directions: *Optional:
Put through blender set at crumb.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine all ingredients together in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for exactly 2 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat for 1 1/2 minutes.
Spread on cake.

title: crab quiche loraine
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat and bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes, until mixture sets and crust is light brown.

title: cherry cheese cups
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together well with beater.
Pour into aluminum foil muffin cups.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven for 5 minutes.
Cakes will fall in center.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Fill center cavity with mixture.
Top with cherry pie filling or jam.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 24.

title: basic cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease skillet or pan.
Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch skillet or one 9-inch square pan.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and chop mushroom stems.
Saute chopped stems and onions in margarine.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add Mozzarella cheese to dry ingredients.
Combine with stems and onions.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.

title: sherbet in the half shell
directions: Halve and juice grapefruits.
Measure 3 cups juice and pulp; set aside.
Pull out and discard membrane from shells; freeze shells.
Combine sugar and water in small saucepan; bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage, 238° on candy thermometer.

title: lentil burgers
directions: Rinse and
drain the lentils and put in medium saucepan with the
water	and
teaspoon
salt.
Cook 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain and discard excess cooking liquid.
Mash lentils. In	a
medium
skillet,
melt 1 tablespoon butter or margarine and add onions and garlic.
Saute until soft, about 2 or
minutes. Stir
in
lentils, along with crumbs, wheat germ, walnuts,
eggs, steak
sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt and hot pepper
sauce.
Shape into
four	patties.
Melt	remaining 2 tablespoons
butter
or margarine and fry patties over medium heat until
brown,
to 5 minutes each side, lifting patties occasionally
with
spatula
to prevent sticking.	Serve with sliced tomato or onion, if desired.

title: healthy baked chicken
directions: In plastic bag, combine crumbs, cheese and spices.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Coat chicken with yogurt, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in greased baking pan.
Optional: Drizzle margarine on top.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve with rice and lemon yogurt sauce.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; cut each breast half into halves. Place chicken pieces, skin sides up, in ungreased rectangular baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover; cook in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, until thickest pieces are done, about 30 minutes longer.

title: "gourmet potatoes"
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream with beater until blended. Add butter to hot mashed potatoes and gradually add potatoes to sour cream mixture.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon into buttered casserole.
Add more butter and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
This can be made 2 days ahead and covered in refrigerator.
Just reheat until piping hot.

title: chicken broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Cook and cut up chicken.
Cook stuffing according to directions.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:
Broccoli, chicken, sliced cheese, soup then stuffing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork and sauerkraut(hungarian szekelygulas)
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil or bacon grease with onion. When brown, add water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Slightly thicken with flour or cornstarch.
Add sauerkraut and sour cream until heated through.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: choux pastry, pate choux
directions: Put water, salt and butter over low heat to dissolve butter, then bring to a brisk boil.
When boiling, add flour.
Remove from heat and beat vigorously until a solid mass forms around the spoon. Cool naturally (not in refrigerator), then beat in eggs, one at a time.
Pipe mixture onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown, light and hollow.
Cool on wire rack. Fill with cream of choice.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and milk.
Then add rhubarb. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until done.

title: date cake
directions: Pour coffee over dates and soda.
Let stand while you mix sugar, margarine and egg.
Add vanilla.
Stir in date mixture and walnuts.
Mix thoroughly with electric mixer.
Add flour mixture. Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack.
When cold, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: tortilla pinwheels(appetizer)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Drop by the spoonfuls onto the tortilla and spread around.
Roll tortilla up.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1/2-inch pinwheels.
Uses about 6 tortillas.

title: mary laybourne's barbecue sauce
directions: Parboil celery and onion for 15 minutes over low heat.
Drain off water, then rinse with cold water.
To celery and onions, add sugar, vinegar, chili sauce, water and spices.
Cook over low to medium heat for 30 minutes.
Stir several times.

title: garlicky beef with peppers
directions: Cut beef in 2-inch strips with the grain.
Cut strips diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch slices.
For ease in cutting, freeze 1 1/2 hours.
Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet until melted.
Add onion, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until onion is tender.
Stir in beef and bell peppers.
Cook and stir about 4 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Stir in wine.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch into beef broth.
Stir into beef mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Serve over noodles.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Shape into meatballs.
Place on baking pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Cool. Makes 30 meatballs.
Can freeze up to 6 months.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix water with chicken soup.
Combine all ingredients and add defrosted potatoes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini stir-fry
directions: Slice the zucchini and potato 1/8-inch thick, then slice lengthwise like shoestrings.
Slice onions in strips.
Cube the bacon.
Put potatoes, bacon and onions in pan and stir-fry about one minute, then add the squash and stir-fry about nine more minutes.
It should be a little crisp.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cooks, before the Civil War, would pinch off pieces of cornbread and give them to the dogs hanging around their open air kitchens to quiet their barking.
As they threw them the small pieces of cornbread, they would call out, "Hush, dogs" or "Hush, puppy," and thence the name for these delicious morsels.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups boiling water.
Defrost strawberries. Stir in strawberries, sugar and salt.
Put in freezer until it begins to gel.
Bake cake.
Mix Cool Whip with Jell-O.
Break cake in half.
Break in pieces, then layer Jell-O mixture.
Break other half in pieces, then layer Jell-O mixture.

title: low-fat lasagne
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, pour 1/3 of the sauce and spread evenly. Layer half the noodles, half the cottage cheese, half the spinach and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Pour another third of the jar of sauce evenly over layers.
Repeat the layers ending with the last third of sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili verde
directions: Dredge meat in flour, fry in oil, add onion and garlic. Cook until onion is soft. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer covered 1 to 2 hours stirring occasionally.

title: papa's blue cheese dressing
directions: Whisk together the mayonnaise, sour cream, plain yogurt, lemon juice, horseradish, Tabasco salt, salt and pepper.
Add Bleu cheese.
Chill.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: In 6-quart saucepan, prepare fettucini as label directs. Drain.
Return fettucini to saucepan.
Over low heat, heat fettucini, cream, butter, salt and pepper.
As you see it come to a boil, add egg and cheese.
Mix well about 1 minute.
Serve immediately.

title: reuben brunch casserole
directions: Pan-fry sausage in medium size nonstick skillet, without adding oil, for 4 minutes.
Drain; reserve.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour into custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in pan of hot water 45 minutes or until knife is clear after inserted.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs; blend well.
Mash bananas.
Add bananas, soda and water.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a 5 x 3 x 11 1/2-inch greased loaf pan.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes until done and cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp and set aside.
Discard skins.
Melt butter over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.

title: zesty oyster crackers
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour over 1 bag oyster crackers and stir on a cookie sheet.
Put in 350° preheated oven.
Cover with foil.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Store in airtight container when cool.

title: oreo mint supreme
directions: Cut marshmallows into pieces and add milk.
Cook over water until melted, mixing with fork.
Do not leave on heat too long or it will get stringy.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: german potato salad
