directions: Boil potatoes in jackets, then peel and cube.
Add cubed onion and celery.
Add salt. Cube bacon and fry until crisp.
Mix vinegar, sugar and water; mix with bacon, then pour over potatoes, celery and onion.
Mix gently.

title: hooper's easy cornbread stuffing
directions: Mix stuffing mix, cornbread crumbs, celery and onion; heat broth and melt butter.
Pour over all and mix.
Put in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or use to stuff turkey.

title: egg and chili casserole
directions: Beat eggs, cottage cheese and butter.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well, then add cheese and chilies.
Beat again and pour into an 8-inch buttered square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until edges are light brown and center firm. This recipe can be doubled in a 9 x 13-inch pan, but will take longer to bake.

title: dad's stir-fry
directions: In wok, saute chicken in peanut oil until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and stir-fry until heated.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Cashews can be added with vegetables if desired.

title: caramel pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut cookie dough into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices in bottom of sprayed pan.
With floured fingers, press dough evenly to form crust.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Meanwhile, in glass measuring cup, combine caramel topping and flour; blend until smooth.
Remove pan from oven.
Sprinkle partially baked crust with pecans, coconut and chocolate chips.
Drizzle with caramel mixture.
Return to oven; bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until topping is bubbly. Cool 1 1/2 hours or until completely cooled.
Cut into bars. Makes 36 bars.

title: zucchini skillet supper
directions: Saute the zucchini and onion in small amount of oil. Add the tomatoes with juice, mushrooms, salt, pepper and oregano to taste, and chicken or ground beef or turkey.
Simmer just until heated through.
Serve in soup bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serves 4 to 5.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; set aside.
Pour half of batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle half of sugar mixture over batter.
Repeat procedure.
Gently swirl batter with a knife.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together; beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Let cool; remove from pan.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Slice cream drops.
Microwave for 1 minute, stir, add milk and peanut butter.
Microwave 1 minute more.
Add pecans quickly and pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.

title: raspberry gelatin mold
directions: Mix in a large bowl the gelatin and boiling water. Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour half the mixture in mold; reserve remainder at room temperature.
About 1 hour later, spread a 16 ounce container sour cream on top of firm gelatin.
Pour remaining gelatin over and refrigerate.
Can be made as much as 2 days in advance.
Can be made with strawberries.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Put cherries in dish.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Pour melted butter over mixture and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash, adding milk.
Add all other ingredients to potatoes.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood spread
directions: Drain shrimp; rinse.
Place in ice water.
Sprinkle gelatin over 2 tablespoons water and set aside.
Combine soup and cream cheese in pan and cook slowly until blended.
Add mayonnaise and blend over heat.
Add dissolved gelatin, shrimp and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into a 5-cup mold coated with cooking spray.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan or cookie sheet.
While cake bakes, melt marshmallows, 1 cup canned milk and 1 cup sugar; add coconut.
Pour over cake as soon as it comes from oven.
Mix butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup canned milk; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 6 ounces chocolate chips and almonds; pour over coconut layer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add the taco seasoning plus 2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish: crushed Doritos, onion, pepper, meat sauce and 1/2 of cheese, sliced.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered.

title: lemony cucumbers
directions: Wash and slice thin 2 medium cucumbers.
Mix in bowl with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 4 hours.

title: peppermint patty drink
directions: Process milk, ice cream and peppermint sprigs in blender. Swirl chocolate syrup in glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown stewing meat.
Combine meat, vegetables and water in crock-pot or large pot.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and thyme.
Add soup bone.
Cook on high for 5 hours or low for 10 hours for crock-pot.
Cook over medium heat for 4 hours on stove. Remove soup bone before serving.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine caramel pieces and flour.
Add apples, caramel topping and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into crust.
Top with pecans.
Bake on preheated baking sheet at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust has browned.

title: applesauce drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients, except oats.
Stir into butter mixture.
Blend in applesauce.
Add raisins and oats.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well; form into ball.
Roll in 2 packages chopped dry beef.

title: jello delight
directions: Fix jello as directed.	Add bananas and pineapple.
Put in refrigerator.
Let jell.

title: wild rice soup
directions: In heavy soup kettle, brown the beef with salt and Italian seasoning, crumbling meat as it cooks.
Add wild rice and 1/2 cup of water, Tabasco, bouillon granules, pepper, celery and onion. Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes.
Stir in the canned soup and remaining water.
Cover and simmer another 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: el rancho baked beans
directions: Brown and crumble meat with onion. Add remaining ingredients. Transfer to large casserole dish and bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Excellent to freeze.

title: german chocolate sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour a 14 x 10 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of chopped nuts and 1 cup of coconut over bottom of pan.

title: luann's banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Mix egg, milk, oil and bananas.
Stir in remaining
ingredients
and mix only until flour is moistened. Bake in greased muffin pans for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut caramel bars
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, heat caramels, water and 1/2 cup peanut butter on high for 1 minute, stir.
Microwave 1 to 2 additional minutes (until melted).
Add Cheerios and peanuts, stir until coated.
Spread in greased 9x13 pan, set aside. In another microwave-safe bowl, heat chips, butter, and remaining peanut butter on high for 30 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Spread over Cheerios mixture.
Refrigerate before cutting.

title: lolly's potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in enough water just to cover, until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir.
Heat again.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Use that juice with enough water to make 3 cups liquid.
Mix liquid with pudding and tapioca and cook until it comes to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Cool before adding sliced bananas.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in blender or by hand; refrigerate.
This dip is best if it sits overnight; it gives the onion a chance to blend into the dip.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In a small bowl, blend all ingredients.
For creamier dip, add more sour cream.
Makes 2 cups.

title: icebox coconut pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks. Beat in sugar, salt, flour and margarine. Pour mixture slowly into the scalded milk.
Cook until thick. Add the vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked
pie shell and put meringue on top.
Brown in oven.
Cool. Put in refrigerator.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat pie filling to a slow boil. Add Jell-O and dissolve. Add pineapple and Coke.
Pour into bowl. Add nuts and refrigerate.

title: dirt cake
directions: Step 1:
Mix pudding and milk until thick.

title: kindergarten unusual jello jigglers(room 3, 1993 - 1994, voted number 2)
directions: Mix unflavored gelatin in 1 cup cold water.
Stir and set aside.
Bring to a boil, 1 cup water in a saucepan.
Add flavored gelatin and sugar.
Bring to a second boil.
Stir, then remove from heat and add the unflavored mixture plus 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir. Pour into greased pan.
Cover.
Refrigerate.
Cut with jiggler shapes when set.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Add salt, baking powder, baking soda, lemon and vanilla extracts, nutmeg and sour cream; mix well.
Add flour and beat.
Chill 3 hours.

title: walking soda
directions: Make a hole in one end of orange.
Put your candy stick in this and suck on it; should be tasty!! (Juice from orange flows through stick.)

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook peppers in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in medium skillet until onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in salt, rice and 1 cup tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
Lightly stuff each pepper with 1/2 cup meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in ungreased baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover for last 15 minutes of baking.

title: cinnamon sugar mix
directions: Mix
together
thoroughly
on slow speed of mixer or by hand. Sprinkle on dough as desired.

title: aunt ginny's liver paste
directions: Cook livers 15 to 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and process in blender.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil. Add remaining sauce ingredients and cook 1/2 hour before adding uncooked meat balls. Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well and put in 1-quart casserole. Cover with chicken.
Mix other ingredients and pour on top of chicken.
Use bread crumbs sauteed in butter or oleo, 2 tablespoons, and 3 tablespoons sharp Cheddar cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until bubbly hot, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked stuffed chicken ball
directions: Skin and trim the chicken breasts.
Pound out until thin. Grate the cheeses and mix together.
Cover your palm with the cheese mixture.
Add 2 to 3 mushrooms with some scallions.
Place another handful of the cheese mixture on top and form into a ball until firm.
Wrap the chicken around the cheese ball (use toothpicks if needed).
Flour, egg wash and pack firmly with the bread crumbs.
Bake in a buttered platter for 13 to 17 minutes at 450°.
Good luck!

title: fresh broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until just tender.
Drain and set aside.
In the same pan, melt butter and blend in flour. Add milk, cooking and stirring, until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add some cream sauce to the eggs; blend and add back to the sauce.
Add spices.
Fold in broccoli and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with saltines and bake 30 minutes.

title: brown slush
directions: Boil sugar and water together; let cool.
Add tea bags to boiling water and steep.
Remove tea bag.
When first mixture is cool, add the cup of tea water, lemonade, orange juice and brandy. Put into container and freeze.
When serving, use ice cream scoop and put into old fashioned glasses.
Fill glass to top.
Pour 7-Up over this and serve with a straw.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cut
eggplant
in
large cubes.
Sprinkle with salt and place in	colander
to
drain.
Cut
remaining
vegetables in wedges
or cubes.
After
eggplant
has
drained
at least 30 minutes, rinse well.
Pour onto several paper towels and blot briefly. Heat about 4 tablespoons of oil in a large stainless steel	pot. Add eggplant and saute.
Set aside.
Add more oil if
necessary and saute onions and peppers.
Add garlic.	Add zucchini.
Saute very
briefly.
Add
seasoning herbs (basil, oregano
and
thyme) to taste.
Add tomato wedges.
Cover pot briefly to draw out tomato juice. Uncover; raise heat and stir constantly
until about 1/2 of juice is left.
Return eggplant to pot.
Can
be
served immediately
or later, warm or cold. Flavor improves as it sits.

title: lazarus chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, oats, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and pecans last.
Drop golf ball size cookies onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cookies will not appear done.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
First cookies, top with ice cream, then fudge sauce.
Sprinkle with nuts and frost.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: custard sauce
directions: Scald milk with vanilla bean in heavy, small nonaluminum saucepan over medium-high heat; set aside.
Combine egg yolks and sugar in a medium bowl; whisk until mixture is thick and lemon colored.
Gradually whisk milk into egg mixture.
Return to saucepan.
Place over low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Set pan in bowl of ice water to cool.
Strain custard into medium bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and cream cheese. Add cooked noodles and milk.
Turn into buttered casserole dish. Mix cornflakes with sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top of noodle pudding.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: braised pork chops
directions: On medium high heat, sear pork chops 2 minutes on each side in oil.
Add water and onions.
Cover and cook 30 minutes on low heat; turning once.
Then add mushrooms.
Cook on low heat for 20 more minutes.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Cool. Drain fruit and add to jello. Fold in other ingredients. Congeal. Serves 20.

title: smothered steak
directions: Rub flour into steak.
Brown on both sides. Season.
Add soup and onions.
Simmer about one hour.
Add a little water as needed.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottoms and 1/2 inch up sides of 2 loaf pans.
Cream the sugar and shortening; add eggs, sour cream and bananas.
Mix until well blended.
Stir into flour just until moist.
Fold in nuts and pour batter into pans. Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until breads test done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring
first 4 ingredients to boil, then cook mixture 6 minutes.
Add 12 ounce jar peanut butter, then add 6 ounce jar peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.	Let stand a couple of hours before cutting.

title: bacon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with chips or crackers.

title: nothings
directions: Beat all ingredients except pie filling in a mixer for 3 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add batter and mark off into 24 squares.
Drop a spoon of pie filling into the center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, butter and white and brown sugars together until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt in mixture.
Add oats.
Form into balls. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: franklin nut cake(aunt ethel miller's traditional christmas cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a tube cake pan and bake at 250°
for 3 hours.

title: rosie's caesar salad
directions: Soak first 2 items together for at least 1/2 hour or more and then take garlic out and throw away. Mix after each ingredient is added. Add 1 hard-boiled egg and 1/4 cup Blue cheese, crumbled. Pour over the top of romaine lettuce; add croutons on top.

title: date-nut pie
directions: Cream together the sugar and margarine; add the next 5 ingredients except the egg whites, then fold in the beaten egg whites.
Put mixture into a 9-inch pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Before serving, may be garnished with a bit of whipped cream.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth.
Pour into muffin paper with vanilla wafers.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Pour cherry mixture on top.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Grease a pie tin and spread out broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a food processor, process quartered onions until finely chopped.
Add 1 cup cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and 2 teaspoons dill weed.
Process until well-blended.

title: party punch
directions: Mix the two juices together with lemonade and just before serving, add 7-Up.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased pan and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
May add 1 can of Green Giant Mexicorn.

title: mother's russia tea(1940)
directions: Put 3 teaspoons mix to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: hot onion appetizers
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet at 150°.
Add soup; stir well. Cut biscuits into quarters; place in skillet.
Cover and cook at 275° about 20 minutes, or until browned, turning once.
Reduce heat to lowest setting; keep warm.

title: yankee barbecue beef
directions: Add to shredded roast beef.
Heat and serve.

title: grandma's egg-topped rice
directions: Fry 1 egg over easy.
Mix on top of rice and add soy sauce. Serves 1.

title: vanilla texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and granulated sugar together.
Bring 1/2 cup margarine, oil and water to a boil; pour over flour mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Beat in eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla, cinnamon, baking soda and buttermilk.
Pour into greased 17 x 11-inch pan and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
(Serves 20.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add grated zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder, mixing well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in chopped walnuts.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add jello and mix well.
Stir in drained fruit. Refrigerate.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Needs no frosting.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake in raw pie crust at 300° for 1 hour.
Mix all ingredients. Put pecans on top.
Makes 1 pie.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with mixer (except nuts) just until mixed.
Do not overmix.
Divide into 2 portions and roll into balls, then roll in nuts.
It helps to put the mixture in the refrigerator for about 45 minutes before trying to form balls.

title: baked rigatoni and ham with four cheeses
directions: Dice the ham.
Grate the Mozzarella, Fontina and Provolone coarsely.
In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter over low heat.
Stir in the flour and cook, stirring frequently, until it bubbles.
Whisk in milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly and continue cooking for a minute.
Stir the ham and cheeses into the sauce.
Heat the oven to 375°.
Cook the rigatoni in boiling salt water until almost done.
Drain and mix with the sauce. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour in the Rigatoni.
Cover loosely with foil and bake until bubbling, about 25 minutes; remove foil.
Heat the broiler; melt the remaining tablespoon butter and toss in bread crumbs. Sprinkle over the rigatoni and broil for about 5 minutes.

title: dressing for fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Good over most any fruit.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple with juice. Add pie filling.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm. Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over salad.
Top with nuts.

title: baked ham gourmet
directions: Cook ham according to directions.
Thirty minutes before ham is done, remove rind and score fat.
Cover with mixture of 1/4 cup Southern Comfort and brown sugar; stud with cloves.
Add mustard to remaining Southern Comfort.
Pour over ham and continue baking, basting occasionally.

title: walleye on the grill
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients together until well blended in a 12-inch long shallow pan.
Dip fillets in sauce.
Sprinkle with celery salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil, cook 5 minutes per side. Serves 4.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in shortening and remove.
Blend flour into the shortening from which the meat was removed.
Add ketchup, water, soy sauce, pepper, bouillon cube, minced garlic and chopped onion. Bring to boil; lower heat to simmer for 20 minutes.
Drop meat into sauce and cook only until tender.
(This much can be done even 2 to 3 days before serving and stored in refrigerator.)
Ten minutes before serving, add fresh mushrooms, pepper rings and onion rings. Cook until crispy-tender, about 10 minutes.
Serve on hot, fluffy rice.
Serves 6.

title: beef stroganoff and noodles
directions: Brown meat in a small amount of oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic; cook until just tender.
Combine soup, sour cream, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms; pour over meat and heat through.
Toss noodles with butter.
Serve meat mixture over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients except ground beef. Mix well. Add ground beef. Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Stir in almonds; mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges of cookies are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: apricot and currant chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken skin side up in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and ginger.
Spread marmalade over chicken and pour apple and orange juice into pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and add dried fruit in juice to pan. Sprinkle fruit with brown sugar and return to oven.
Bake, basting often, 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken and dried fruit to platter.
Pour sauce into gravy boat and serve with chicken.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Top with Swiss cheese.
In separate bowl, combine milk and soup.
Stir well.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Pour butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: busy day cheesecake
directions: Soften and cream the cream cheese.
Beat with 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add pudding and rest of milk; beat well.
Spread into crust. Add canned cherries or blueberries on top. Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put the apples in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Add water and lemon juice.
Mix flour, brown sugar and cinnamon in bowl. Cut butter into dry ingredients with pastry blender or two knives until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; top with a mixture of 2 cups crushed corn flakes or potato chips and melted butter.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberries in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine egg, flour and sugar.
Stir until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle over blueberries.

title: kir punch
directions: In large
pitcher,
combine
wine
and creme de cassis. Gradually add
the carbonated water.
Stir gently to mix.
Add ice cubes and serve in wine glasses.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions. (For best results, use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex cake dish.)
When done and still warm, poke holes over the top using a fork.
Mix caramel topping and evaporated milk together and pour into holes.
When cake is cool, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: layered salad
directions: Chop lettuce for bottom layer.
Chop cauliflower for 2nd layer.
Cheese on 3rd layer.
Bacon on 4th layer.

title: crazy crust pizza dinner
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir until blended, about 70 strokes.
Spread batter thinly on bottom and thickly up sides to 1/4-inch of pan rim.
Add your favorite toppings.
Bake in a 425° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: pepperoni pizza mac
directions: Mix milk, egg and seasonings with cooked macaroni.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Layer remaining ingredients and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Can omit or add any pizza type ingredients.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour or until firm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Place bread cubes and sausage in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend all other ingredients and pour over sausage and bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May prepare and refrigerate overnight, baking when ready to serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Sift flour and dry ingredients together. Cut in (blend) shortening. Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Roll out on floured board and cut into biscuits. Let rise. Place on a greased pan and bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: jiffy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients at one time.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sicilian-style lemon chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts until almost done.
(I use an indoor grill.)
Mix the remaining
ingredients.
Put the chicken breasts in a baking dish, and pour the lemon sauce over top.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini(low-fat recipe)
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Mix milk with cornstarch in a separate saucepan; add chicken broth, pepper, salt, onion salt and nutmeg; heat over low heat, stirring until thickened.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Boil noodles according to package directions and drain.
Mix noodles and mushrooms in the sauce and add 3 cups cooked chicken pieces.
Turn into a baking dish and top with 3 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven until browned, about 20 minutes.
Serve from casserole.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given with water.
Put in 3 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: texas cake
directions: In large bowl mix flour and sugar.
Bring to boil: butter, shortening, cocoa and water.
Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar.
Mix until blended.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed. (Batter will be bubbly and thin.) Bake at 350° in 11 x 17 x 1-inch greased pan for 20 minutes.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown meat with the onion and season to taste.
Add the mixed vegetables, mushroom
soup,
cream
of
celery
soup and Cheddar cheese.
Heat somewhat and put in pie pan with crust. Place crust on top and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: duck dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and white bread.
Add celery, onion, cream of chicken soup, sage and eggs.
Pour hot broth over all and stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Prick pie crust several times with a fork. Arrange apples in pie crust. In bowl, combine next 9 ingredients. Spread mixture over apples. In bowl, combine all topping ingredients. Pour over the top of pie. Bake 1 hour.

title: no crust german chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, melt chocolate and butter or margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and cool.

title: regenia's punch
directions: Cut lemons, limes and oranges in half and squeeze juice into large container.
Stir in sugar.
Put fruit into container with juice.
Pour warm tea over fruit and let sit overnight.
Strain liquid from fruit and add orange pineapple juice, ginger ale and cherries.

title: sweet `n' sour beans
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove to paper towels. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings. In the drippings, saute onions until tender. Add brown sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard, and garlic powder. Bring to a boil. In a slow cooker, combine beans and peas. Add onion mixture and bacon; mix well. Cover and cook on high for 3/4 hours or until heated through. Yield: 15-20 servings.

title: calico cole slaw
directions: Stir all ingredients together and chill at least 1 hour.
The longer it chills, the better the flavor.

title: sausage and brown rice casserole
directions: Cook and stir sausage in Dutch oven until brown; drain.
Stir in rice, milk, celery, green pepper, onion, soup and mushrooms. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until center is bubbly, 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potatoes 'n cheese
directions: Cool the boiled potatoes and grate.
Mix cheese and grated potatoes.
Add the sour cream and salt; mix.
Add the onion. Place mixture in a baking dish and dot with butter on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour or until a brown crust starts to appear.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Combine the shortening, sugars, vanilla and water; beat until creamy.
Beat in the eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Place 8 slices of bread in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread with ham and grated cheese.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Beat eggs; add milk, dry mustard and salt.
Pour over bread and allow to set overnight, in refrigerator, covered.

title: chinese stir-fry
directions: Saute ginger and garlic in oil for 3 minutes. Remove the ginger.
Add 1/4 cup water, tamari and all the vegetables.
Stir over medium heat for about 5 to 7 minutes. Add rice.
Stir over medium heat until all ingredients are combined and heated through. Add tamari to taste.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together and add to mixture. Roll into balls. Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400° on cookie sheet.

title: fabulous yeast rolls
directions: Scald in pan the milk, sugar and shortening.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in water and add to milk mixture.
Add enough flour to make a thin batter.
You can use a mixture for this part.
Cover and set aside until double in size.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Two cups of flour will be good at this time.

You may have to add more to make a soft dough consistency. You may store this in refrigerator a couple of days, but make sure your container is much larger than the dough mixture and is oiled and covered tightly.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in casserole dish.
Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain.
Add to rice.
Saute onion in margarine; add soups and cheese.
Pour over rice and veggie mixture and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: western beans
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add sugars and seasonings.
Add beans; mix well.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: light biscuits
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; cut in the margarine with a pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles course meal.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead, 4 to 5 times.
Roll dough to a 1/2 in. thickness and cut with a 2 in. biscuit cutter.
Place on an ungreased pan and bake at 425 degrees for 12 minutes or until browned as desired.
Yields 24 biscuits.
One biscuit equals 60 calories (1 starch), 1.5 grams fat, 120 mg sodium with use of salt, (80 mg sodium without salt), 1 mg cholesterol.

title: miniature coffee cakes
directions: In bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and vanilla pudding; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and milk; beat until blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon batter into greased paper-lined 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups until 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with walnut topping.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans; cool slightly.
Serve warm. Or, cool completely on wire racks and serve cold.

title: fried meat
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make patties (2-inches thick). Cook without oil ten minutes each side.
Add tomatoes, lettuce and pickles.
Add to hamburger buns.

title: grandma sawyer's old time fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture, mixing well.
Stir in fig preserves and grated orange.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Grandma always used her hands to mix it together real good.
Bake in a greased tube pan in a 300° oven for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: yellow cake
directions: Bake cake; let cool.
Cook pineapple and sugar together until thick.
Punch holes in cooled cake, then pour this mix on top of cake.
Mix pudding with milk until rather thick.
When cool, spread with Cool Whip and coconut on top.

title: mary's pumpkin apple bread
directions: Instead of spices and canned pumpkin, you can substitute canned pumpkin pie filling.

title: maki's fried rice
directions: Fry bacon.
When done, remove bacon and pour off some of the grease; pour beaten eggs into pan and scramble; remove eggs.
Add oil to pan and turn on high.
Add diced onion.
Stir 1 minute; add chopped green pepper and grated carrots.
Quickly stir for 2 minutes.
Return the eggs and crumbled bacon to pan.
Stir briefly.
Reduce heat to medium-high.
Add rice and heat thoroughly.
Add salt, Accent and black pepper.
Mix well.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer chicken and broccoli in bottom of large baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for half an hour, stirring once halfway through.
Serve warm with French bread.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine egg, milk, sugar, baking powder, flour and salt in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Heat 1-inch of oil to 375° in electric skillet.
Spoon 1/2 cup batter at a time into funnel, closing spout with finger.
Drizzle batter into spiral in hot oil. Fry until brown on both sides, turning once.
Garnish with confectioners sugar or fruit.
Makes 6 servings.

title: glen's venison roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Salt and pepper. Cover with water. Turn on high until it begins to boil.
Peel and cut potatoes in quarters. Slice onion. Chop the carrots and place on top of the meat.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: italian chocolate cookies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Use no eggs.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add dry ingredients with evaporated milk and the 1/2 can of water if mixture is too dry.
Then add chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Make balls (roll like a meatball), not too big.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes and cool.
Frost with chocolate frosting and sprinkles if you want.

title: deep dish chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large saucepan, cook celery in butter until tender. Stir in flour, bouillon and pepper.
Add 4 1/2 cups milk. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in chicken, carrots, potatoes and peas.
Remove from heat.
In medium bowl, combine remaining milk and biscuit mix.
Mix well.
Turn 2/3 of the dough into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with flour.
With floured hands, pat evenly over bottom and sides of dish.
Pour chicken mixture into prepared dish. Turn remaining dough onto a well floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut into 8 (3-inch) rounds.
Arrange on top of casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is golden. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: ice pops
directions: Pour fruit punch into the ice tray, then put plastic wrap over the ice tray.
Stick popsicle sticks through the plastic and freeze.
Freeze for about three to four hours and then serve.

title: bacon cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, peanut butter and vanilla and form into balls.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: angel corn muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add liquids to dry mix.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Makes approximately 18 muffins.

title: window cleaner
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a clean gallon jug.
Add enough water to make a gallon.
Transfer to spray bottles and get someone to clean your windows and mirrors.

title: don's sweet 'n sour bits and pieces
directions: Brown sausage as directed on the package.
Cut each sausage into 4 or 5 bite size pieces; set aside.
Brown kielbasa and ham pieces in the sausage skillet.
Add pineapple, including juice, the sweet and sour sauce and the meats, heating thoroughly.
You may place in a baking dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with mixer 2 minutes. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 5 minutes, then glaze in pan.

title: yeast buns
directions: Mix.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Set 2 hours. Make into buns.
Set 2 hours and bake.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Add spaghetti to chicken broth.
Cook until tender.
Drain. Add chicken to spaghetti; set aside.
Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add mushrooms, mushroom soup, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Mix well with chicken and spaghetti. Place in greased baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese and olive canape(appetizer)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread on party rye; broil until bubbly.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Beat together all ingredients with electric mixer. Makes about 1 cup. Refrigerate unused portion. Use as dip for apple wedges.

title: rolled chicken breasts with pecorino romano
directions: In a saucepan, over medium-high heat, bring all of the ingredients to the boil.
Turn down the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: oats and raisin cookies
directions: Cream honey, sugar, butter and egg.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together, then stir into creamed mixture.
Add oats and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: molasses cookies(two dozen)
directions: Combine oil, sugar and molasses together.
Add egg and then dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: sausage 'n' cheese tarts
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble; drain and set aside. Combine biscuit mix, butter and boiling water.
Stir well.
Press about 1 tablespoon of dough into bottom and up sides of well-greased and floured muffin cups. Spoon sausage evenly into cups.
Combine egg, half and half and green onions.
Stir well. Spoon about 1 tablespoon egg mixture into each cup.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over each tart; bake an additional 5 minutes.
If desired, garnish platter with tomato rose and parsley.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: sure way to make kraut
directions: Chop cabbage.
Wash in cold water.
Pack washed cabbage into canning jars and set aside.
Mix salt and vinegar in saucepan until salt is melted (do not boil).
Add gallon of cold water to salt and vinegar mixture.
Fill jars with mixture and seal jars.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp.
Add shrimp last.
Make 24 hours ahead.
Refrigerate.

title: clams delmarva
directions: Reserve liquid and chop meat of steamed clams in coarse bits. Add to these chopped canned clams, divide between 24 half shells. Add teaspoon of liquid to each shell, sprinkle bacon and bell pepper on top and top with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° for 14 minutes.
Place under broiler and brown.
Serve immediately.

title: avocados stuffed with lobster
directions: Cut avocados in half lengthwise and remove seed.
Bruise slightly and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Don't peel.

title: spam spread and olive mold
directions: Mix Spam spread with olives; add dry mustard and Tabasco to taste.
Pack into gelatin mold or cup.
Chill until just before serving with crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Dice and spread bananas over crumbs.
Mix powdered sugar and other stick of melted margarine with vanilla and eggs.
Beat well and pour over bananas.
Drain pineapple and spread over top.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle coconut and nuts over top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach and water chestnuts.
Chop onion and chestnuts. Mix all ingredients together.
Cut out middle of Hawaiian King bread.
Spoon spinach dip in center of bread.
Slice to serve.

title: best zucchini bars
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Frost with cream cheese icing.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: jewel fruit cake
directions: Simmer raisins and water for 3 minutes, just until water is absorbed.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Blend in egg.
Dissolve the soda with the hot water, add this to applesauce and blend into creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Add in gumdrops and nuts.
Blend this into creamed mixture; add cooled raisins.
Pour into greased and lined (3 thicknesses of wax paper) loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours.
Cut when cool.

title: beef pilaf
directions: Cut beef in small pieces.
Put in 5-quart kettle with onion, celery and seasonings.
Cover with water; bring to a boil and stir to mix well.
Reduce heat to a simmer.
Cook until meat is tender, then add tomato paste and stir; bring to a boil.
Add about 6 cups water; let come to a boil.
Add rice and cook until rice is done, about 1/2 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla. Sift flour in mix.
Stir into banana mix.
Alternate with milk. Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: aloha cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and milk with electric mixer until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Stir in nuts; pour over crust.
Return to oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Loosen cake; cool before removing.
Chill in refrigerator.
Drain pineapple and add kiwi; arrange decoratively on top of cake.

title: consomme rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Add rice, almonds, consomme and water.
Bake covered for 35 minutes.
Stir.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 5 or 6.
(Good with roast or chicken.)

title: mary's quick brownies
directions: Use one pan for all.
Double recipe for cookie sheet.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour alternating with whipping cream (do not beat cream first), beating after each.
Beat in vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Bake in tube pan or Bundt pan.

title: sour cream fudge cake
directions: Sift together cake flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add shortening and cream or buttermilk.
Beat at low speed and then add unsweetened chocolate, eggs, vanilla and hot water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: edith's cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onions and peppers. Mix all other ingredients. Heat until sugar is dissolved; cool completely. Pour over vegetables. Mix well. Put in covered jar. Refrigerate.

title: chinese vegetable salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oil, pickle juice, salt and pepper.
Heat until sugar melts.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine celery and onions and chill in cold water 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine beans, peas, pimento and almonds.
Drain water off celery and onions and mix everything together with sugar-oil-vinegar mix; refrigerate.
Will last several days.

title: giant chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine.
Make big balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring and salt.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Cut up, lengthwise, 6 to 8 cloves of fresh garlic.
Pierce lamb and insert pieces of garlic.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on lamb generously.
Sprinkle rosemary on lamb. Place in large roasting pan, pour can of beef broth into the pan. Add all the potatoes and onions around roast.
Put pan into 500° oven and immediately turn down oven to 325°.
Bake about 30 minutes per pound.
Occasionally baste and turn potatoes and onions. Serve with the mint jelly on the side.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.

title: beef skillet fiesta(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Brown meat in oil over high heat in skillet.
Break meat up or leave in coarse chunks.
Add onion.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until onion is tender, but not browned.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn, beans and bouillon.
Bring to a boil and cook until vegetables are done.
Stir in green pepper.
Boil again.
Stir in rice.
If using instant rice, remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
If using Uncle Ben's regular rice, cook all ingredients together 25 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness. Inside chicken, place 2 tablespoons of green chilies and 1 piece of cheese.
Roll chicken around chilies and cheese.
Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over venison as a marinade. Allow to stand overnight.
Place venison strips on cookie sheets or foil in a 175° oven.
Bake for approximately 2 hours or until dry.
Be sure to leave door of oven open a crack.

title: easy homemade rolls
directions: Put the shortening into a large bowl and pour the boiling water over the shortening.
To this, add sugar and salt; mix and cool to 105° to 115°.
Mix yeast with 1/2 cup water (105° to 115°) and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Mix and let bubble.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add eggs to cooled shortening mixture, then add yeast mixture and flour last.
Mix well on mixer or by hand.
Cover and set in refrigerator 1 1/2 to 2 hours or up to 1 week.
Take out and shape in favorite rolls.
Spread with melted butter.
Let rise until double in size. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Also makes great cinnamon rolls.

title: blue ribbon icebox cookies(my favorite cookies and easy!)
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugars.
Add beaten eggs.
Add spices and vanilla.
Add flour and soda, sifted together.
Add dates and nuts.
Shape into rolls in waxed paper or Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate the rolls until needed.
(Keep indefinitely.)
Slice more than 1/4-inch thick when you slice them.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Yum!!

title: cheese, pepper and herb-stuffed pork chops
directions: To cut pockets in chops, place on cutting board and with a sharp knife, cut horizontally through each chop nearly to the bone.
Stir together cheese, red bell pepper, rosemary and thyme. Divide mixture into 4 portions, stuffing 1 portion in each pocket.
Close pockets with small skewers or wooden picks.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat source for 14 to 18 minutes, turning once. (Grill by placing on grid over medium coals.
Grill 16 to 18 minutes, turning once, until pork is cooked through, but still slightly pink.) Season with salt and pepper, if desired.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook carrots, mushrooms or cauliflower until soft in water. Let stand until cold.
Slice in pieces.
Cover with water 1/2 way up.
Add oil, white vinegar, salt, pepper and onion.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters; keep liquid.
Spread a layer of cracker crumbs in baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 the oysters, 1/2 the butter and sprinkle with pepper.
Make a second layer of the same; cover with milk and oyster juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done.

title: easy potato dish
directions: Spread potatoes in 9x13 pan.
Add onions and drizzle with melted butter.
Salt and pepper.
Mix soup, sour cream and cheese whiz.
Spread over potatoes.
Sprinkle cornflakes over potatoes. Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Stir butter into spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs. Form crust from this into a 10-inch pie plate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; mix together, except cherries and Dream Whip. Beat Dream Whip.
Mix together and spread some over top, then top with cherries.
For best results, let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: When chicken breasts are cooked, remove from water and allow to cool. Cut into bite-sized pieces. In a bowl, mix soup with can of milk until well blended. In a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, layer dressing, then chicken, then soup mixture. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Uncover casserole and continue to cook for another 1/2 hour. Great with a salad and rolls.

title: asian beef noodles
directions: Stack beef steaks, cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
In medium bowl, combine beef, jalapeno pepper and oil; toss to coat.
Break noodles into 4 pieces; reserve seasoning packet.
Cook noodles as package directs; drain.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar and put on cooled pretzels.
Refrigerate.
Mix jello, boiling water, cold water and strawberries and when cool pour over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.
It's rich, you may want to serve as a dessert!

title: zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan; stir well.
Bring mixture to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Use as a basting sauce for chicken or pork during cooking.
Yields 7 1/2 cups.

title: pizza potatoes - microwave
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and cook 10 minutes on High power.
Stir in pepperoni and cheese. Cover and heat for 10 minutes on High power.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes after cooking before serving.

title: lemon jello
directions: Leave until partially set.
Add 1 can lemon pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts (optional).

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: In a large bowl, blend mayonnaise, oil, honey and mustard. Whisk in vinegar, then cayenne and mix until smooth. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, marshmallows, oleo, milk and cocoa to a boil. Stir for 1 minute, then stir in peanut butter.
Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Completely dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside.
Mix Crisco, sugar and boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Add flour and yeast alternately, mixing thoroughly. Cover and let rise until double.
Flatten on lightly floured board until about 1/2-inch thick.
(More flour may be added if needed to make dough handle easier.)

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix
and
bake	in
9 x 13-inch pan about 10 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender (15 minutes) and drain well.
Mix rest of ingredients in bowl.
Fold in squash. Melt 3/4 stick of butter in frying pan and add stuffing mix.
Add salt and pepper; stir well.
Pack most of the stuffing into the bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Add squash mixture; put rest of stuffing on top.
Dot with remaining butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add 1 cup fruit cocktail and juice.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top of raw batter the brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Mix well beaten egg, margarine, salt, sugar and dates in a saucepan; cook on very low heat until dates are nearly dissolved, stirring so that it doesn't scorch.
Remove from heat.
Let mixture cool until you can handle it.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts. Mix well.
Make small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: grilled apricot ham
directions: In a small bowl, combine apricot spread, mustard and vinegar. Grill ham steak over hot coals, brushing occasionally with sauce, until browned on both sides, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raspberry, cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix
and
pour
of mixture (of about 7 cups) into a container;
let set.
Layer 1 pint sour cream and add the other 1/2 mixture.
Let set.
This makes quite a lot.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat until frothy and add rum and half and half.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Heat first four ingredients over low flame until melted and set aside.

title: potato pancakes(from overrock inn)
directions: Combine all ingredients and fry in 1/2-inch of grease until brown on both sides.
Serve with hot spiced applesauce or sour cream.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain and arrange in ungreased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain and arrange on noodles. Flake tuna and sprinkle over spinach; top with cheese.
Combine milk, eggs and salt; beat well.
Pour over casserole mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes or until center is set.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: caramel rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add Rice Krispies.
Spread on a buttered cookie sheet (9 x 13-inch too small).

title: working girl's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain off fat, then add soups and cook until meat is done.
Meanwhile, cook Creamettes according to package instructions.
Mix all together and serve as is or add cheese and bake in oven until cheese is melted.

title: noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Chop and fry bacon and onion, salt and pepper.
Pour sugar over noodles and mix.
Grease frying pan with butter or oleo.
Add bread crumbs.
After browning, put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peach cake
directions: Crumble and mix first 5 ingredients together like a pie crust, then add next 2 ingredients.
Stir until mixed well (use a fork), dough will be sticky.
Put dough in a greased 10 1/2 x 15-inch sheet pan.
Place sliced peaches on top.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine
thawed
and drained vegetable mix with 1/2 cup cheese, sour
cream,
pepper, pimento and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour
into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 30	minutes.
Top
with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered five minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in the pineapple.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip until evenly mixed.
Chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off excess grease.
Melt stick of butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with frozen hash brown patties.
Mix milk and eggs together and season with salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over hash browns.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Cover pan with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.

title: mrs. doc's old time egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, cornstarch and vanilla.
Beat.
Add milk and blend well.
Pour in pie shell. Place in preheated oven.
Immediately reduce temperature to 350°. Bake for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: quickie tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Delicious for tuna lovers!

title: steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into 5 or 6 serving pieces.
Place in slow cooker or crock-pot.
Add other listed ingredients and cook on low for 8 hours. Serve over mashed potatoes or noodles.
Rice is also good.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt one stick of margarine. Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk until well blended.
Pour over melted margarine that is in baking dish. Then place fruit on top of this.
Pour juice over all of this slowly and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Cook hamburger meat with salt and pepper until done; drain. Saute onion in oil; add to meat.
Mix in tomato sauce and beans. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Warm tortillas in microwave until soft. Place tinfoil in 2-inch pan and pour half of Ragu sauce on bottom. Spread and fill tortillas with meat and bean mixture and place in pan.
Place a little of each cheese in each.
Pour remaining Ragu over enchiladas and top with remaining cheese.
Turn foil up so that juice will not leak out.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook onion, mushrooms and garlic 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in spinach, oregano and basil. Blend cottage cheese, egg whites and shredded Mozzarella cheese. Layer noodles, spinach, cheese and tomato sauce.
Bake at 375° in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 servings (200 calories and 4 g. fat).

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix nuts, sugar, and syrup in iron skillet.
Boil over medium heat until honey color and nuts split open (15 or 20 minutes). Take off heat, stir in soda.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs.
Beat on high for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup of flour and beat 1 minute.
Add flavoring and mix.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mom's minute fudge
directions: Cook.
When it come to a full rolling boil (3 minutes), add vanilla and beat until it becomes thick.
Pour into buttered pan (13 x 9-inch).

title: cereal nut mix
directions: Mix cereal and nuts together; set aside. Mix margarine, syrup, sugar and salt together.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture begins to boil. Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour slowly over cereal and nut mixture; stir until coated.
Bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes. Stir and bake 15 more minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet on medium/high.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add remaining scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettuccine; toss and heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the oats mixture and sifted dry ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a greased loaf or square pan for 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Pour on topping and put in oven for 5 minutes.

title: pineapple refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup margarine and the granulated sugar.
Press half of the crumb mixture firmly in ungreased, square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Beat the powdered sugar, 1/2 cup margarine and the egg in a small mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Spread carefully over crumb mix.
Fold pineapple into Cool Whip; spread over sugar mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over top.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours or until firm. Cut into squares and top with Cool Whip and cherry.

title: muscadine or scuppernong jam
directions: Separate pulp from skins of grapes.
If desired, chop skin in food blender or chopper.
Cook skins gently 15 to 20 minutes, adding only enough water to prevent sticking (approximately 1/2 cup).
Cook pulp without water until soft.
Press through sieve to remove seeds.
Combine pulp, skins and sugar.
Bring slowly to boiling, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves.
Cook rapidly almost to jelling point, about 10 minutes.
As mixture thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Pour hot jam into jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: no crust cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until light and creamy (the longer it is beaten, the lighter the cake).
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add sugar and extract, beat until smooth, thick and lemon colored.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan and bake 50 minutes at 375°.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: frozen ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients with a mixer; place in a freezer bowl and freeze for 2 hours.
Makes a delicious frozen treat for any occasion.

title: powdered sugar substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Whip until well blended and powdered.

title: sylvia's italian-style vegetable quiche(made 3,000 times.  hated by my children but loved by all others.)
directions: Saute onion.
Cook or steam one of the vegetables.
Mix vegetables with sauteed onion.
Beat eggs.
Mix eggs, grated Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese together in large bowl. Combine onion-vegetable mix and cheese mix.
Pour in ready-made pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(Can freeze, uncooked.)
Cool and serve.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir together.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out third of dough to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured cutting board. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool and cut in bite size pieces.
Layer in punch bowl: cake, pudding, peanut butter cup, Cool Whip, cake, pudding, peanut butter cup and Cool Whip.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice well.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shells and chill before serving.

title: utterly deadly southern pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together 2 or 3 minutes.
Beat eggs (not too stiff); pour in slowly the hot syrup.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Turn into raw pie shell and bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes, or until set.

title: blender custard pie
directions: Set oven
at
Blend
all
together at high speed. Pour in a
9-inch
deep pie crust, unbaked.
Bake at 450° until brown on top.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake until the middle of pie shakes like jello.
Remove right then (this is important); if you overcook this pie it will be watery.

title: pecan pie
directions: Chill pie shell.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, syrup, salt, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes; garnish with whole nuts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Using a large heavy iron skillet, melt oleo over medium heat. Stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour syrup over popped corn and peanuts.
Toss or stir (syrup will be sticky).

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and oleo.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.

title: sausage squash special
directions: Cook sausage and garlic until meat is brown; drain off excess fat.
Cook squash, covered, in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Stir squash and next 6 ingredients into meat; fold in eggs.
Transfer to 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: burritos
directions: Mix ground beef and refried beans with taco seasoning; warm on stove.
Roll mixture in flour tortillas; add cheese on top of mixture in tortillas.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: italian vegalinks
directions: Brown onion and potatoes in oil or margarine over medium heat. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: country budget meat balls
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Add meat, salt and pepper. Shape into meatballs and put into casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir until just blended.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Top each slice with a dollop of whipped cream and a slice of banana.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Beat by hand.
Sift flour; add cocoa, salt and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Next add vanilla and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour marshmallows on cake.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Spread icing over cake.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over very low heat, then let cool. Sift flour with salt. Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Cream margarine; gradually add sugar and continue beating until well blended and fluffy. Blend in chocolate; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add flour and salt mixture, blending well. Next, add soda and buttermilk mixture and blend well. Pour mixture into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool layers and frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: pita pocket sandwiches
directions: Brown, then drain the ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add 1 cup water and the next five ingredients; mix well, cooking at medium-high heat.
Blend water into cornstarch; stir into meat mixture, cooking until thick.

title: best yet pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening (Crisco) until it resembles fine crumbs.
Add cold water.
May be refrigerated several days or wonderful to put in freezer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushroom caps and chop up fine.
Combine Prosciutto, cheese, breadcrumbs, mushroom stems, parsley, salt and pepper to taste and egg.
Spread dressing evenly inside mushroom caps.
Place in single layer in a baking dish and pour oil over the top.
Add 1/4 cup of hot water to baking dish.
Bake uncovered in 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, blend first 5 ingredients.
Add bread mix; stir well.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool.
If desired, frost with confectioners sugar icing.

title: sicilian quiche
directions: Bake pastry shell at 450° for 8 minutes.
Be sure to prick shell before baking.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Arrange a layer of 1/2 the cheese, 1/2 the tomatoes, 1/2 the onion and green pepper mixture and 1/2 the salami into the baked pie shell. Repeat layers.
Beat eggs; stir in milk and remaining ingredients. Pour over layers in pastry shell; bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°; bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until set.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow baking pan.
Mix rest of ingredients well.
Pour over chicken.
Let set for 2 or more hours.
Pierce with fork before baking at 375° until brown.
Pour off some sauce and pour back over, all while hot.
Cover with foil for 1 1/2 hours or until tender at 350°.
Same recipe can be used with spareribs.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Split peppers in half, horizontally; remove seeds and membranes.
Wash and blanch in boiling water for 2 minutes and set aside.

title: jello salad
directions: Boil pineapple juice 2 minutes. Add a little sugar. Add buttermilk and cool. Add remaining ingredients. Cut in squares or mold.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix well; bake in a 400° oven, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken taco bake
directions: Cook ground chicken, onion and garlic powder until done. Add tomatoes, taco seasoning, soup and noodles. Put in large casserole and top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake until cheese melts, at 350° to 375°.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture; beat smooth with a wire whisk.
Test mixture to see if it flows easily through a funnel or out of a pitcher.
If too thick, add milk; if too thin, add flour.

title: custard refrigerated fruit cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Mix together next 3 ingredients smoothly, pour over crumb crust; bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Mix berry mix and juice. Spread on baked cake.
Spread Cool Whip or whipped cream on top; refrigerate overnight.

title: rice with mushrooms
directions: Prepare onion soup.
Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine. Mix all together well.
Bake for 1 or 1 1/2 hours at 325° until well done.

title: dinner surprise special
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese and sausage as directed on packages.
Combine together.
Serve.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add chocolate chips, candy bar and nuts.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add jello, stirring until dissolved. Add fruit.
Pour half into an oblong pan and chill until set.
Let remainder stand at room temperature.
When the first half is set, spread it with sour cream.
Top with remaining fruit mixture and chill again.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix 2/3 cup sugar and frozen lemonade.
Let stand while baking cake.
Mix jello in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Put cake mix in mixing bowl.
Add oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add gelatin mixture to cake batter.
Grease tube pan; pour in mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
When done, pour lemonade mixture on cake whole still hot.

title: susie's vegetable stew
directions: Chop onion and bacon with ground beef; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Serve with hot cornbread!

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Corn bread will come to the top and form crust.

title: lynne's vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: cheese spread
directions: Bring to a boil eggs, sugar, vinegar, flour and salt.
Add remaining ingredients to hot mixture.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Add potatoes and garlic to boiling water.
Cover and boil slowly about 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving cooking liquid.
Put hot potatoes and garlic through food ricer.
Add salt, pepper, butter and cream.
Stir to blend ingredients.
Add reserved potato cooking water to desired consistency.
Serves 6.

title: judy suggs' chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients.
Beat and pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients to make crumb mixture; reserve 3/4 cup.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar and garlic into a sauce.
Marinate wings for 24 hours.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: angel sweets
directions: Melt chips and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat. Blend in egg (beaten).
Stir in sugar, nuts and marshmallows, blending well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut and chill.
Makes about 48.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and cook on top of stove until cheese and broccoli melts and mixes.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour or longer.

title: pork steaks
directions: Brown steaks in lard.
Remove steaks from pan and arrange in shallow casserole or baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a slice of onion, a slice of tomato and a slice of green pepper on each steak.
Cover and return to oven for another 15 minutes.

title: blueberry peach coffee cake
directions: Wash blueberries and drain with peaches.
In a small bowl combine sugar, flour, butter and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix muffin batter by box directions, except do not fold in blueberries. Spread batter into 8-inch square pan.
Top with fruit.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices. Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Gradually add molasses, beating constantly.
Blend in flour, using low speed on mixer.
Add water; mix until smooth.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 9 servings.
May be topped with whipped cream.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn bread mix, eggs, corn and oil and set aside.
Brown meat and drain.
Grease large iron skillet and heat.
Sprinkle meal to brown.
Pour batter on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add meat, onions and pepper.
Pour remaining batter on top and bake in oven until brown.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt.
Beat well.
Set aside after stirring in chocolate chips.

title: stuffed celery hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cream the Roquefort and cream cheese together.
Fill crisp celery stalks 2-inches long with this mixture.
Then with a knife, make a narrow lengthwise trench through the center of each filled celery stalk.
Fill the trench with a small quantity of caviar. Then cover it over with some of the cheese mixture, making it rounded.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: peanut butter oatmeal bars
directions: Mix oleo and sugar together; add peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Add egg and milk to mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour, soda, salt and oats.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost.

title: my mom's sicilian potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs and onion.
Add oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix well and allow to chill.
This dish is easy and delicious.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients into ungreased pan, 8 or 9-inch square. Make 3 wells and add liquids in each.
Pour water over all.
Mix with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges together.
Add sugar and nuts. Mix well.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Good with meats.

title: penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Combine soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil. Pour over carrots.
Place onion and pepper on top.
Do not cook onion and pepper.
Will keep for several days.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package.
Add carrots and celery.
Combine soup, milk and parsley; set aside.
In 3-quart baking dish, arrange stuffing in center. Spoon along the sides, the soup mixture in a thin layer.
Arrange chicken over soup mixture.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes more or until chicken is tender.

title: frosty orange cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine water, juice concentrate, ReaLemon and sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves. Chill.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Thoroughly combine crushed strawberries, yogurt and Cool Whip in a bowl.
Spoon into a graham cracker pie shell and freeze for 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator for 30 minutes (or longer for softer texture) before serving.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Makes one pie.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Boil chicken until done; take chicken and place on a plate and let cool.
Remove meat.
Bring chicken broth to a boil and add macaroni; cook until done.
Drain some broth off if too much is still in pan once macaroni is done (save it just in case).
Mix soups together and add to macaroni; add chicken meat.
Stir until soups are well blended.
Add a little broth, if needed, to make a thick gravy-like sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: granola bars
directions: Toast oats in an ungreased large shallow baking pan in moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine toasted oats with rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Press firmly into well greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and simmer until rhubarb is tender (or 4 to 5 minutes).
Remove foam. Add box of Jell-O and stir until mixed.
Cool and put in jars. Cover with paraffin.

title: spicy vegetable dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a double boiler and mix well.
Cook over boiling water until thick. When still somewhat runny, cool and put in container. Refrigerate.
It will thicken when cool. Serve as dip for vegetables.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fruit rolls
directions: In small saucepan combine fruit, water, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand about 15 minutes or until cool.
Stir.
Meanwhile, wrap tortilla halves tightly in foil.
