Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Remove half of tortilla halves from foil.
Keep remaining tortilla halves wrapped until needed.
Spoon a tablespoon of fruit along cut edge with milk.
Press gently to seal.
Place tortilla rolls, seam side down, about 1 inch apart in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Brush lightly with milk.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar if desired.
Yield:

title: raw rhubarb cake
directions: Mix well, put into 9 X 13 pan.	Sprinkle cinnamon & sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: betty's minestrone soup
directions: Add all ingredients to large stock pot.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach squares
directions: Beat eggs.
Add spinach, butter, milk, cheese and onion. Blend in flour and dry ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: creamed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender. In a bowl, mix mayonnaise, yogurt, onion flakes, cayenne and salt.
Serve sauce over broccoli.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peach dessert
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and jello in pot, add water.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly until thick.
Put in refrigerator until it is cool.
Stir in peaches.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: peanut butter fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Make crust and place in 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: michigan rocks
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Check cookies to see if they are done.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: In large skillet, brown meatballs; drain.
Meanwhile, combine reserved pineapple liquid, lemon, sugar, soy sauce and ginger. Add cornstarch.
Mix well.
Pour over meatballs.
Add green peppers.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes, covered.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Mix peach Jell-O with boiling water, then add cold water, pineapple and peach pie filling.
Congeal.
Mix the sugar, sour cream and softened cream cheese by hand.
Spread on top of congealed mixture.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma eichhorn's potato salad(recipe dated about 1910)
directions: Pour vinegar over eggs; add mustard.
When thoroughly mixed, add to potatoes and salt.
Beat all together and add onion.

title: candied green beans
directions: Fry bacon; drain all fat off.
Remove all liquid from beans. Put beans, margarine, mushrooms and brown sugar in bacon.
Cook on low heat for about 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Throw all the ingredients in a big bowl and stir with a wire whip. Drop by tablespoons onto a hot, greased frying pan. Turn when you see bubbles "exploding" on the top that isn't cooked. Keep on greasing the pan or they will stick.
This makes enough pancakes for a hungry teenaged boy and a friend who might have stayed overnight.
Top with lots of butter and syrup or homemade jam. (Strawberry is the best.)
If your friend is still hungry, make another batch. They taste the best if your mom makes them.

title: darby's chicken breasts
directions: Place the chicken on the ham and roll up.
Hold this in place with toothpicks.
Place in shallow baking dish and cover with
the Durkee
and soup, mixed together.	Cover the baking dish with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.	Serves 6.
More breasts can be added.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Place applesauce in small saucepan and heat over medium heat until bubbly. Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Cool, then stir 7-Up and mix well. Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: baked steak
directions: Mix salt, pepper and flour.
Roll steak pieces in mixture. Cook onion and steak until nicely browned.
Put meat in casserole. Add soup and water to skillet.
Stir until all brown residue from meat is mixed with the liquid.
Pour over meat in casserole and cover tightly.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Very good.

title: frozen peppermint pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in crushed peppermint candy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie crusts.
Cover.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish as desired.
Freeze leftovers.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, mustard, tomato paste and barbecue sauce.
Add this to beef mixture; crumble bacon into all.
Add pork and beans; simmer for 10 minutes on top of stove.
Pour into casserole dish; cook at 325° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Mix together and roll out in different shapes (with hands). Bake on greased cookie sheets at 350° about 14 minutes.

title: orange honey cream cheese spread
directions: Place cream cheese in microwave dish; heat on Defrost for 1 or 2 minutes to soften. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into serving dishes or put into pastry bag and pipe it onto one plate or individual plates. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: nitey-nite cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until stiff. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop cookies by teaspoon onto a foil covered cookie sheet.
Place in oven.
Turn off oven.
Leave cookies in oven overnight and don't peek.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Coat frying pan with layer of vegetable oil; heat to medium-high.
Pour in batter.
Will cover most of pan bottom; flip when brown.

title: chicken cordon bleu(serves 6)
directions: Make a white sauce by melting butter over low heat.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add chicken bouillon cube and stir until dissolved.

title: easy sour cream potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large mixing bowl.
Stir in soup, sour cream and milk.
Blend well.
Stir in onion and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese. Break potatoes apart, but don't thaw.
Add to mixture and stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Combine sugar and 1/3 cup of water in medium saucepan.
Slowly bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover and simmer on low heat while beating egg whites.

title: layered turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Stir in zucchini, carrot, bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Saute until vegetables are softened, 4 to 5 minutes; set aside.
In large bowl, combine turkey and next 6 ingredients.
Press 1/3 turkey mixture into prepared pan.
Spread half the vegetable mixture over turkey, pressing down.
Repeat with remaining turkey and vegetables, ending with turkey.
Cover pan with foil; bake until loaf has shrunk from edges of pan and juices run clear, about 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes, drain.
To remove, invert pan over serving plate.
Garnish, if desired, with zucchini and carrot slivers.
Serves 6.

title: olive spread
directions: Mash cream cheese and mix well with remaining ingredients.
Put in pint jar and refrigerate at least 24 hours until thickened. Serve on thin toast, any kind of cracker or as a finger sandwich filling.
Keeps well.

title: baked ziti
directions: Season the ground beef with the garlic salt. Brown the ground beef in a skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain well. Add the ziti and spaghetti sauce and mix well. Spoon into a 9x13 baking dish. Top with the cheese. Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti-pizza style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and milk together; toss with spaghetti.
Spread spaghetti mixture in a greased jelly roll pan or roasting pan (11 x 18-inch).
Top with sauce.
Arrange pepperoni slices in rows over sauce; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: spinach stuffed fish fillets with parsley rice
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, prepare rice.
Boil 15 minutes in 8 cups water. Rinse and cover. Keep warm in oven.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Bring
pineapple
and
sugar to boil and stir in jello. Cool. Add buttermilk.
Then stir in Cool Whip and nuts.
Easy to make and very good!

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture is coarse.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Transfer to lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly, roll dough out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 475° until golden brown, about 15 to 18 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Saute sausage until browned. Drain well. Separate crescent rolls into triangles. Place on pizza pan. Press together to form crust. Spoon sausage over dough. Sprinkle hash brown potatoes over sausage. Pour eggs mixed with milk, salt and pepper over top. Shake pan to settle eggs evenly over crust. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until center is done.

title: cool banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese; blend until smooth. Make pudding according to directions, but use only 2 1/2 cups of milk (instead of 3 cups); mix with cream cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Add banana extract.
Use large dish.
Layer pudding, wafers and bananas.
Refrigerate.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Add 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water to each cherry, lime and orange jello.
Pour into 3 pie plates and let chill at least 4 hours.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen until tender; debone when cool.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Add chicken fat, milk and beaten egg. Form dough; roll out and cut into strips.
Drop into boiling broth. Cook dumplings until tender.
Add chicken and sliced, boiled eggs. Serves 6.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese with brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Before serving, drizzle caramel sauce and chopped pecans over top.

title: artichoke chili pepper dip
directions: Mix all and put into pan.
Heat through.
Serve with chips, etc.

title: kringla bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Pour in milk.
Mix soda, salt and flour.
Work into liquid to make cookie dough.
Cut into strips.
Makes the strips into figure 8's or knots.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: river chili
directions: Place meat, onion and garlic in large, heavy fry pan. Cook over medium heat until the meat is lightly browned. Add oregano, comino seed, chili powder, tomatoes, hot pepper sauce, salt and hot water. Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer about 1 hour.

title: coleslaw(quick and easy)
directions: Dice carrot.
Slice and chop cabbage.
Mix all other ingredients together and stir into the vegetables.

title: chow mein
directions: Put beef, pork and whole pieces of chicken in small amount of water.
When tender, remove chicken from bones; skin and dice. Combine diced chicken with beef and pork.
Bring to boil, then add onions, celery and pepper.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then add bean sprouts, bamboo shoots and water chestnuts; cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and soy sauce; mix well.
Then add beaded molasses to mixture.
Put this mixture in chow mein and stir constantly until thickens.
Serve hot over noodles.

title: famous fudge
directions: Combine margarine, evaporated milk, sugar, and salt in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, nuts, vanilla. Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.

title: squash pie
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.
When coconut is left out, this pie tastes like an old-fashioned egg custard.

title: chicken with cherries(serves 6)
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Combine flour, salt, garlic salt and paprika in paper or plastic bag.
Add 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time; shake.
Heat butter or margarine in skillet.
Brown chicken slowly in butter, turning once.
Drain cherries.
Add cherries to chicken.
Pour wine over all.
Cover; simmer 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve with rice.

title: caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a rectangular pan.
Heat caramels and milk in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat; stir frequently until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Mix flour, brown sugar, soda, salt and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in butter with a fork until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of the crumb mixture into the pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts; drizzle with caramel. Press remaining crumb mixture over the top; bake until golden brown, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes; cut into bars.

title: low sugar marble cake(originally by grandma reggie!)
directions: *Consistency is the key.
On humid or dry days, batter should flow but still be thick.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients and use 3 tablespoons for 1 cup hot chocolate.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together beans and taco sauce, then mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Mix everything together. Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Form balls and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Pour over meat balls. Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Sprinkle part of crushed corn flakes on bottom of pan.
Place chopped cabbage over corn flakes.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and milk; bring to boil.
Do not add water.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle cheese over top, add remaining corn flakes with 1/2 stick butter. Bake at 325° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add pimento, shrimp and soups, mixing gently.
Add all seasonings.
Stir in rice.
Pour into 9 x 13 dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, then top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake to melt cheese.

title: hometown baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for at least 1 to 1 1/2 hours until top layer is baked, crusted and nicely browned.

title: drop paczki
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop large tablespoonful into hot grease (about 375°).
Turn constantly.
Allow to cool and sprinkle with powdered or regular sugar.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove the crust from bread and set aside.
Arrange bread slices in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken. Cover with mushrooms and water chestnuts.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over bread cubes; cool.
Add melted butter, sugar, eggs, salt, raisins and cinnamon.
Place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and set in a pan of hot water.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until knife comes out clean.

title: low calorie cheesecake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust according to package directions; omit sugar and use low calorie margarine where it calls for butter.
Add 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon; press into square 10 x 10-inch pan.
Chill or can be baked for 5 minutes in 350° oven.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Empty peas, Shoe Peg corn, green beans, celery, onion and pimentos into a large glass bowl.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand 15 minutes (room temperature).
Refrigerate several hours.

title: coffee punch(as served at missouri governor's mansion)
directions: Stir coffee and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Add milk and vanilla.
Chill.
Pour over ice cream in punch bowl.
Top with dabs of whipped cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 30 servings.

title: apricot delight
directions: Crush chocolate wafers.
Put half of wafer crumbs in 8-inch square pan.
Add 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar to butter.
Add eggs and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and beat hard.
Spread over chocolate wafer crumbs.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and water. Add pudding mix. Beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon in 1 cup pudding mixture in glass dish or bowl. Top with wafers and bananas. Repeat layers, ending with pudding.

title: chili crock-pot
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and let it cook all day on low.
Spray crock-pot with Pam before cooking.
If chili without beans is preferred, omit beans and increase meat to 3 pounds.

title: fuddpuckers
directions: Cut package of cookie dough in half after unwrapping.
Cut each half into 5 slices and cut each slice into 4 pieces.
Drop each piece into a greased mini muffin cup.
Bake according to package directions or until golden brown.
Press a peanut butter candy into each cookie as soon as they come out of oven.
When chocolate starts to melt slightly, sprinkle with chopped pecans. When completely cool, remove from pans.

title: cheese straws
directions: Work cheese, salt, pepper and flour into butter with hands. Place in large star shaped cake decorator tube.
Shape straws on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Yields about 80 straws.

title: banana milkshake for one
directions: Place banana, orange juice and skim milk in blender.
Blend for 1 or 2 seconds until smooth.
Stir in yogurt.
Chill, if desired, then serve.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: Mix yolks, vinegar, tarragon and parsley in small saucepan under the lowest setting.
Stir 1/2 the butter with wooden spoon until it melts.
Then repeat with the other 1/2 of the butter. Remove from heat when it begins to thicken.
Serve over asparagus or red meats.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix ingredients and form 6 patties.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix remaining soup with 1/3 cup water.
Pour mixture over meat and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured pan (tube) at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool while making glaze.

title: six minute pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: old fashioned pickled wieners
directions: Slice each wiener into 3 pieces.
Combine with onion and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a pan.
Bring this mixture to a boil and boil about 3 minutes.
Pour over the wieners and onions.
Put in jars and cover tightly.
Refrigerate for several days before you serve them to let spices and pickling syrup penetrate.
This makes a nice big batch and it will keep for several months in your refrigerator.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water according to package instructions.
Add remaining ingredients except paprika and mix.
Place in greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes uncovered.
Serves 4 - 6.

title: golden macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well.
Set aside.
Place milk, flour, and onion salt in a quart jar; cover tightly, and shake vigorously 1 minute. Stir together flour mixture, 3-1/2 cups cheese, and macaroni.
Pour macaroni mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Sprinkle evenly with breadcrumbs and remaining 1 cup cheese; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spray the dish with nonstick coating (9 x 9; double recipe for 13 x 9).
Spread a little of the soup on the bottom (do not dilute).
Layer the asparagus over the top and sprinkle with lemon pepper seasoning.
Layer hard-boiled eggs and cover with remaining soup.
Repeat layers and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cook for 30 minutes (or until bubbly) at 375°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery

title: microwave peanut brittle(great for gifts.)
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar and corn syrup together in 2-quart microwave dish.
Cook on High 8 minutes.
Stir halfway through with wooden spoon.
After 8 minutes, remove.
Add vanilla and butter; stir well.
Cook on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Mixture should be darkened.
Add soda and stir quickly.
Will foam.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Spread fast and thin.
Cool 1 hour.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: luscious fruits
directions: Drain all cans of fruit.
Mix with other fruits.
Mix whipped topping according to package directions.
Fold fruit into whipped topping.
Garnish with sliced kiwi fruit.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Reserve several berries to garnish.
Blend remainder with orange juice until smooth and strain into saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with a little of mixture and add to remaining mixture in pan.
Heat, stirring until it comes to a boil, then cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add sugar, lemon juice and buttermilk.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve in chilled bowls; garnish with extra strawberries and parsley.
Sesame wafers go well with it.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Fry bacon slowly, drain and crumble.
Saute onion in bacon fat.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over slow heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar and water. Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in potatoes and bacon.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blackened mahi-mahi with pineapple salsa
directions: For salsa, mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chipped beef dip and pumpernickel
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill. Serve with pumpernickel bread. Pull the middle out of loaf and tear apart and put dip in the middle or you can serve with crackers.

title: refrigerator rolls(an old southern recipe)
directions: Cut the recipe in half to do in food processor.

title: vegetarian stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers until softened, but still slightly firm.
Cook broccoli, onion and cauliflower in boiling water until tender. Drain.
Add bread crumbs, cheese and salsa to moisten (a little water may be added if needed).
Fill peppers with mixture and bake until cheese melts.

title: creamy thousand island dressing(good with lettuce or cabbage)
directions: Combine salad dressing, chili sauce, Worcestershire, Tabasco, salt and paprika in 1-quart bowl.
Stir in celery, relish, olives, onion and egg; mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Chill.
Makes 1 pint.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Put first four ingredients in greased dish.
Blend or mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over rest and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Add nuts and marshmallows. Mix with chocolate.
Roll in coconut and chill overnight.
Next morning, slice in slices.

title: soufleed corn
directions: Melt butter and sugar and add flour slowly.
Gradually blend in milk, then add beaten eggs, then baking powder.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into a greased baking dish (1 1/2-quart).

title: meat loaf with tomatoes
directions: Mix the ground beef, rolled oats or bread crumbs, green pepper, onion and cheese.
Add 1/2 cup or more tomato sauce, mixing well.
Shape into a meat loaf or pack into a loaf pan. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
If you use the veal-beef-pork mixture, bake at 325° for an additional 30 minutes. Serve with more tomato sauce on the individual portions.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until crust is brown and custard is firm.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread evenly on hamburger rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Now mix well.
Bake until tests done.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour, cocoa and spices.
Add this alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture, then add apple.
Cook in 3 layers in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato patties
directions: Cook potatoes in peeling until done.
Peel and mash potatoes. Add margarine, brown sugar, coconut and flavoring.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out and make into patties.
Put pineapple rings on top of the patty.
Place marshmallow in the pineapple ring.
Put in oven until marshmallows are brown.
Makes 12 patties.

title: pink lady dessert
directions: Heat pineapple to dissolve Jell-O, then mix in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Don't have to use mixer.
Use as salad or dessert.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat second 3 ingredients together and spread over pretzel layer.
Mix last 2 ingredients.
Cool until semi-formed.
Then spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix sour cream and salad dressing together well.
Blend bacon bits, onion bits and the vegetables carefully.
Add salad dressing and sour cream mixture.
Chill overnight or for a few hours.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat the eggs and add other ingredients; pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake until it thickens, about 350°.

title: wiener-bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first four ingredients. Add the vinegar and beat for 4 minutes. Add the oil; beat for 10 minutes. Add poppy seeds; beat for 5 minutes. Yield: 2 3/4 cups.
This is delicious served with fresh fruit salads.

title: peach tea
directions: To each cup of hot water, add 2 teaspoons of mixture, or more if desired.

title: dole pineapple spinach salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 1/2 cup of juice for dressing.
Mix pineapple with bacon, spinach, celery and onion.
Combine reserved juice with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Add to salad and toss.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt together and add 1 can Eagle Brand milk.
Bring to a boil and remove from stove.
Cool.
Don't refrigerate.

title: lemon angel cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.

Cook egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind and gelatin over hot water until it coats a spoon. Beat egg whites stiffly with sugar and add to mixture. Break angel food cake (either homemade or bakery cake) into bite size pieces.
Oil an angel food cake pan and alternate layers of cake with sauce.
Chill overnight and serve with whipped cream frosting.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cool and creamy cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine in small bowl, then press in the bottom of pie pan; set aside.
Put gelatin in cold water.
Stir over low heat until dissolved. Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and salt, mixing at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually add milk, lemon juice and gelatin.
Chill until slightly thick.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over crust.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: brenda's favorite chicken salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing together.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour dressing over other ingredients and toss gently.
If salad seems dry, add extra Ranch dressing.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the steak, onion and garlic in the butter.
Remove the garlic.
Stir in the soup, water, sour cream, paprika, salt and pepper. Cover.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until steak is tender, stirring frequently. Serve over cooked noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple topping for lemon cake
directions: Mix all together and cook until thickened.
Cool to serve on cake (enough for one large cake).
Very good!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together in a large casserole dish the zucchini, 2 cans onion rings, soup, onion and 2 packages of cheese.
Mix well. Sprinkle top with 1 can onion rings and 1 package cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave parmesan chicken
directions: Mix tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic salt in a 2-cup measuring cup.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Reduce power to Medium for 5 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook shells (small) or linguini spaghetti according to directions.
Mix onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Add cut vegetables to pasta, then add Italian dressing and Durkee salad dressing.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar, 3/4 cup peanut butter and milk.
Fold in 9 ounces whipped topping.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Freeze 2 hours.
Spread with remaining peanut butter and top with whipped topping.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Next, add salt and spices and milk; mix well.
Beat egg whites at room temperature on high for 1 minute; gradually add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until stiff and forms a peak.
Fold in the egg whites into sweet potato mixture.
Spoon mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until set.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Heat until bubly.
Serve warm with taco chips for dipping.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, salt and soda; add.
Add creamed mixture to bananas, vanilla and pecans.
Stir until moistened.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves or 1 Bundt pan.

title: chicken with onions
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper. Add onions.
Mix soup and sherry and pour over all.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Refrigerate for several hours.
When ready to cook, put in 350° oven, covered, and cook for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 30 to 45 minutes longer.

title: banana carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and mashed banana.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves; mix well.
Add carrots, oatmeal and nuts.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in 9-inch pan.

title: no fuss lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef in large skillet over medium heat until brown.
Drain; add spaghetti sauce and tomatoes to skillet, stirring to combine.
Set aside.
Combine Ricotta (or cottage cheese), egg, Parmesan cheese and basil.
Spread 2 cups beef mixture over bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Arrange lasagna noodles in a single layer.
Spoon Ricotta cheese mixture on top of noodles.
Sprinkle with one cup Mozzarella cheese and top with beef mixture; add remaining lasagna noodles.
Top with Ricotta cheese mixture and top with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cover lightly with foil in tent fashion and let stand for 15 minutes before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar and continue beating.
Add nuts and chocolate chips. Stir well. Drop by teaspoon on a foil-lined pan and place in hot oven. Turn oven off. Forget them for 4 hours. Remove from oven. Cookies are ready to eat.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Combine
Bisquick, sugar, baking powder
and
cornmeal. Add eggs, milk and melted margarine to the
batter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or muffin pan.
Bake at
350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 24 pieces or 36 muffins.

title: cherry delight
directions: Set aside 1/4 of the crumb wafers.
Mix together remainder of crumbs, powdered sugar, melted margarine and egg yolks.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan the crumb mixture.
Place cherry pie filling on top.
Cover with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a deep casserole dish.
Combine flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Then pour batter on top of butter.
Do not stir!
On top of batter, pour 2 cups fruit that includes its juice, such as peaches, pears and berries that are sweetened to your taste.
Do not stir!
Cook about 30 minutes or until it is golden brown at a temperature of 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Place in layers in buttered baking dish, sprinkling each layer with cheese, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour milk around edge.

title: spiced apple rings
directions: Combine water, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon sticks, cloves, allspice and food coloring in large kettle or skillet.
Bring to boiling over high heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cut apples crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut out core of each slice with canape or hors d'oeuvre cutter.
Place slices in skillet.
Cook 5 minutes. Cool.

title: onion dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand at least 1 hour. Serve with chips or vegetables. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pea soup
directions: Soak beans 4 hours or overnight.
Discard water.
Dice potatoes (skin on), celery, carrots and onion.
Add ham.
Put in 6-quart pot.
Cover ingredients with water.
Simmer 4 hour.
Remove ham. Remove fat and bone.
Cut ham into bite-size pieces.
Return to soup.
To thin, cook longer.
To thicken, add water.
Serve with toasted bagels.

title: spinach crepes
directions: Cook and cool spinach.
Stir in sour cream and crumbs.
Put 2 tablespoons of spinach mixture in each crepe.
Roll and place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brush crepes with melted butter, sprinkle with cheese and bacon (you may use almonds instead).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated and bake for 25 minutes.
Makes 10 to 15 crepes.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake (light)
directions: Sprinkle crushed chocolate wafers in bottom of a 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: eggplant-cheese casserole
directions: In a large frying pan, heat oil, add onions, mushrooms and green pepper.
Saute over medium heat until vegetables are limp, about 5 minutes.

Stir in eggplant, tomatoes, salt and parsley. Cover and simmer slowly, about 25 minutes, stirring often. Uncover and increase heat briefly, if needed to reduce liquid. Meanwhile, combine both cheeses and eggs.
Spoon half the eggplant mixture into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with half the cheese mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese mixture. Bake, uncovered, in 275° oven for about 25 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook chopped onions and celery in oleo or oil until transparent.
Add vinegar, lemon juice and chicken stock and cook a little longer.
Add catsup and brown sugar; simmer 30 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add mustard and Worcestershire sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into 6 well-greased 10-ounce custard cups. Place on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: giblet gravy
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients and add salt and pepper to taste cooking on medium heat.
Gravy can be thickened by adding 2 Tbsp. of cornstarch to 1/2 cup of chicken broth;
add this mixture slowly while stirring to get desired thickness.

title: rancher's pie
directions: Melt butter. Add all ingredients. Mix well. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned and set.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Over medium gas flame, steam broccoli until partially cooked, about 3 minutes.
Turn off flame; cool and press dry.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs and milk until frothy.
In separate bowl, thoroughly mix flour, baking powder and salt; stir into egg mixture, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese and onion; spoon into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, spreading evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° gas oven for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand for 5 minutes and cut into bite-sized pieces. Yield:
4 dozen (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: big batch cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine
cake
mix,
yeast,
cup flour and salt in a large bowl.
Stir
in
water,
eggs
and oil.
Beat at medium speed with
an
electric
mixer for 2 minutes.
Gradually add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover dough and let rise. Divide dough in half.
Roll each half 15 x 14-inches
and spread with butter or margarine.
Mix sugar and cinnamon
as
you
desire and sprinkle over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice
and let
rise.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Then glaze with powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.

title: bachelor button cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat well and add egg. Combine dry ingredients into butter mixture.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Chill for easy handling.
Make into small balls and dip into granulated sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Press down with greased or oiled fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Bake in the middle of the oven.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Whip until fluffy.
Add milk while continuing to beat until well blended. Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before glazing pie.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, syrup and salt to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the soda.
Drizzle mixture over the popped corn in a large roaster.
Bake for 3/4 hour in 200° oven.
Stir often to separate.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, well beaten, then flour, salt, vanilla, syrup and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for about 25 minutes longer.
(Some recipes bake at 375° the full time.)

title: old-fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Continue cooking, stirring almost constantly to hard ball stage (260°) or until a small amount of mixture forms a hard ball when tested in very cold water.
Remove from heat; quickly add butter and blend.
Slowly pour over popped corn in large bowl while mixing well.
Form into balls, using as little pressure as possible.
Butter hands, if desired.
Makes 15, about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.

title: herb cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine carrot and water.
Heat to boiling; remove from heat.
Add stuffing; toss to moisten.
Cool slightly.
Stir in cheese.
Brush each mushroom with margarine.
On 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan, arrange mushrooms.
Spoon rounded mixture into each mushroom cap.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms. Break stems off and chop finely. Melt 4 tablespoons margarine and lightly saut stems, bread crumbs, onion, parsley and seasonings. Blend with eggs. Butter pan. Brush mushrooms in and out with butter. Stuff and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix dry ingredients, gradually adding the milk and a well beaten egg.
Beat thoroughly and then add melted butter and corn. Drop by spoonfuls into hot, deep fat and fry until well browned. Drain on brown paper.

title: deluxe seafood chowder
directions: Cut fish into 1-inch chunks.
In 3-quart pan, saute onion in the butter until tender, but not brown.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until softened.
Combine soup, water and Cheez Whiz in separate bowl.
Thaw broccoli.
Cook rice according to directions.
Combine all ingredients in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into bite sized pieces. Combine with bacon, raisins and onion.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli mixture and toss. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving, tossing occasionally.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Mix all ingredients except lemon juice, honey and salt.
Whiz momentarily in blender or shake well in a jar.
Pour over lemon, honey and salt mixture and allow to marinate in refrigerator for 6 hours or overnight.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Peel and cut in half the 5 peaches.
Mix together flour and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over pastry in pie pan.
Arrange peaches, cut side up in sugar mixture.
Mix together, milk and egg, beat slightly and pour over peaches.
Mix together 1/3 cup sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg and sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes; until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: ambrosia salad mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measure liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Stir in Cool Whip with wire whip until blended.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture mounds.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut. Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm. Unmold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chemi cheri sauce
directions: Mix in wine bottle and season according to taste.
Let set 24 hours.
Use as barbecue sauce on ribs or chicken.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, place sugars, eggs, oatmeal and vanilla. Pour margarine over ingredients.
Blend for about 5 minutes with an electric mixer.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, then add the veggies, chopped (quantities are approximate, and you can adjust the veggies-to-liquid portions to suit your taste).
Chill for at least 3 to 4 hours (about 8 is best).

title: cabbage bundles
directions: Mix these ingredients well and form into balls.
Cut core from large head of cabbage; submerge in boiling water in large kettle. Let stand 10 minutes until leaves are softened.
Remove leaves and wrap a large leaf around each meatball.
Place leftover cabbage leaves in bottom of 6-quart kettle, then place bundles on top. Add 2 cans tomato soup and about 1/4 cup catsup.
Add water if needed and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: microwave stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from clean mushrooms; chop stems finely.
Add onion to stems; microwave uncovered on High for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Blend in cheese.
Mash; mix well.
Add bread crumbs and bacon; mix well.
Fill caps of mushrooms; arrange in 8-inch round pan.
Microwave uncovered on High for 3 to 4 minutes, turning dish once.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown beef with onions. Add onion salt, garlic salt and all other ingredients except corn and potato. Simmer on low heat about 1 hour. Add corn and cook for 15 minutes (be sure to stir, because corn will stick). Grate Irish potato and add to stew to thicken. Cook until potato is done. Easy to freeze, just let cool and put in containers.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water; add to dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and mix like biscuit dough.
Fold out and cut like biscuits.
Melt in bottom of pan and dip biscuits in melted butter (I use 1 stick of butter).
Fold in half and place close together in pan.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes at 425°.

title: caramel sauce and apples
directions: Mix all together; microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir. Microwave 5 more minutes or until sugar melts.
Serve with sliced Granny Smith apples, dipped in orange juice.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: In a
pot,
add
an
even amount of water to 1-quart of berries; bring to
a
boil.
Turn down to medium heat and cook for 5 minutes.	In
a
large
bowl, melt 1 stick of margarine. In another bowl,
mix flour and sugar; add to that mixture 3/4 cup milk.
Pour
this
batter into melted butter; stir and add sweetened berries with juice.
Stir a few times.
Bake in oven at 350°
for
to
50 minutes.
Fifteen minutes into baking time, stir once and sprinkle with sugar.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Combine flour, 2 cups sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat at least 5 minutes.
The batter will be very thick.
Core, peel and very thinly slice apples.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Grease and flour tube pan. Alternate cinnamon/sugar, apples and batter (in that order), 1/3 of each at a time.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix flour and dry ingredients.
Stir in walnuts, raisins and apples.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour to mixture and work together.
Place in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
While cake is baking, make frosting.

title: rajonette's barbecue sauce
directions: To make Rodney, LeJon and Lynnette's own homemade barbecue sauce, just throw everything in same pot and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine with eggs until smooth.
Add salt to flour along with baking soda.
Mix alternately with flour mix until all used.
Beat until smooth, adding the flavorings. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour batter in pan; place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on cake plate.

title: green onion gravy
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine or butter in medium skillet.
Add 3 to 4 chopped green onions.
Simmer, then add salt and flour; add 1 cup milk (not necessary) and water for consistency.
Use for taste Worcestershire or soy sauce.
(A few dashes should be enough.)
Let simmer until you reach desired consistency.

title: sausage treats
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and let it set for about 30 minutes.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes or until sausage is done.

title: supper omelet
directions: Sprinkle this over omelet while cooking slowly.
Run spatula around edge to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
When egg is almost cooked, but still shiny, loosen edge; roll or fold one-half over.
Serve at once.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Thaw strawberries. Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, grate carrot and chop green pepper finely.
Add salt to cabbage and allow to stand 1 hour. Drain well.
Add carrot and pepper and mix.
Heat remaining ingredients until sugar dissolves. Cool.
Pour over slaw and freeze in containers.
Makes 12 servings.

title: creamy tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Mix noodles, tuna, soup, mushrooms, sour cream, milk and pepper in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine.
Sprinkle over tuna mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. When done, sprinkle with parsley.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in 4 cups boiling water and salt.
Drain.
Mix milk with egg, beating until mixed.
Layer macaroni and cheese alternately in casserole dish, ending with plenty of cheese on top.
Pour milk mixture over this and bake for approximately 25 minutes.
Do not bake too long as it will be dry.
Bake just long enough for the mixture to become bubbly.
This is a favorite of my grandchildren.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine peanut butter, margarine, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add 2 eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Then add flour, baking powder and salt.

title: texas grits
directions: Bring water to boil; add grits while stirring.
Lower heat to medium when grits have turned water white.
Take off heat and add egg, slowly so white blends in, stirring constantly.
Add cheese. Butter 9 x 10-inch dish.
Pour grits in dish and cook in oven at 375° until center is firm.

title: walk to school cookies
directions: Mix with hands.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add cream cheese and chopped pecans. Add frozen strawberries to the hot jello and have the cheese either cubed or made into balls with the nuts. I usually just cube the cheese and add the nuts alone. This will almost set up while you stir in the cheese and nuts.

title: shrimp and egg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with Miracle Whip.

title: chicken desiree
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Top with cheese slices.
Spoon mixture of soup and wine over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix; drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve with rice or Rice-A-Roni.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: layered casserole
directions: Layer potatoes in an oiled baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread corn; sprinkle with pepper, onion and carrots. Crumble beef over top.
Sprinkle again with salt and pepper.
Top with tomato sauce; spread evenly.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes. Top with cheese and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown flour and chili powder in oil.
Stir in water gradually. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Brown chops and remove.
Add onion and the next 4 ingredients and saute.
Remove 1/2 of these vegetables; set aside.
Add tomatoes, hot sauce and pepper to remaining vegetables in pan. Combine cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water.
Add to vegetables. Cover; cook for 1 minute on medium heat.
Stir and mix.
Put chops in pan; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir other half vegetables in rice.
Serve chops over rice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add the egg.
In another bowl, mix the sugar, shortening and boiling water until all the shortening has melted smoothly into the mixture.
Allow to cool slightly, then add to the yeast mixture.
Mix all liquids together.
Fold in flour and salt.
Stir until thoroughly mixed. Allow to rise until double in size.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix thoroughly the cornmeal, flour, salt and baking powder. Add slowly the boiling water, a small amount at a time, until the mixture is damp but not runny.
Add eggs; beat and add chopped vegetables and jalapenos if desired.
Drop by spoonful into hot grease (deep fat) that fish were fried in, until golden brown.

title: akara(fried bean cakes)
directions: Soak peas in cold water for a few minutes.
Dehusk peas by grating in a blender for a few seconds.
Add water and peas to a large bowl; drain water and black-eyes.
Repeat several times until black-eyes and husks are removed.
Blend the peas until very fine. The mixture should be thick.
Finely chop onion and add to the blended peas.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat oil and, using a spoon, scoop small portions into the oil and deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with custard, cereals or Quaker oats for breakfast.
It can also be served as an entree for dinner or eaten as a snack.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Put in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: strawberry glace' pie
directions: Bake and cool pie
shell.
Wash
and hull strawberries. Cut up one cup berries.
Mix
sugar
and cornstarch in 2 quart saucepan. Stir in water
until
smooth.
Add
cut up berries. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Stir in food coloring; cool.
Arrange
remaining
whole berries in pie crust.
Pour cooked berries
over
them.
Chill
until
firm, about three hours.
Garnish with whipped cream or topping.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix well by hand, take a small ball of dough and put out real thin.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 30 minutes. Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: vegetable hash
directions: Cook turnip and potato until tender; drain and remove to bowl. Put broth in skillet.
Cook onion and pepper over medium heat for about 4 minutes.
Add corn, turnip and potato; toss with thyme, salt, pepper and 3 tablespoons parsley.
Coat heavy skillet with olive oil spray.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes, until bottom is golden.

title: french hot chocolate
directions: In double boiler over hot, not boiling water, heat chocolate and corn syrup until melted and smooth. Stir occasionally with rubber spatula. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes or until cool. Stir in vanilla.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Wash peas thoroughly and cover with cold water and let soak overnight.
Put peas in large pot, covered in water, bring to boil.
In frying pan, add small amount of cooking oil.
Add onion and celery until slightly brown.
Add to peas.
Add diced ham to peas.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour longer.

title: bacon ranch potato salad
directions: Microwave potatoes until done and add other ingredients.

title: country scrambled eggs
directions: Microwave:
In 3-quart casserole, microwave bacon on High until softened (2 1/2 to 3 minutes).
Add potatoes.
Cover; microwave on High, stirring after half the time, until potatoes are crisp-tender (5 to 8 minutes).
Stir in onions and green pepper.
Cover; microwave on High, stirring halfway, until crisp-tender, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Stir together remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour egg mixture over vegetables; stir to blend. Cover; microwave on High, stirring halfway, until eggs are just dry and set, 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; let stand until cheese melts.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add black pepper to taste. Simmer over VERY LOW heat. Add small amount of milk for desired thickness. Serve hot.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Arrange rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1 cup sugar and dab with bits of butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add alternately with milk.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: minestrone a la valentino
directions: Saute garlic, celery, onion and carrots in oil, just until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add thyme, oregano, bay leaves, tomato puree and water.
Bring to a boil and add spinach, green beans, peas and kidney beans.
Bring mixture to a boil again and add pasta shells.
Reduce heat and simmer mixture, just until shells are cooked.
Do not overcook.
Discard bay leaves and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: paprika cream schnitzel
directions: Fry bacon until done, then add veal, which has been cut into portions and brown in hot bacon fat.
Add onions and brown, then season well with paprika and salt.
Stir in sour cream and tomato sauce.
Cover pan and cook about 20 minutes.
Serve cutlets covered with the sauce.

title: wheat germ bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, yeast, wheat germ and salt. Gradually stir in 1 1/4 cups flour, more or less, by hand; add enough to make a stiff batter.
Cover and let rise until light and doubled.
Stir down and place in a greased 2-quart casserole or loaf pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until deep golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: salmon hash
directions: Cook sliced potato in boiling water, 5 to 6 minutes, until tender.
Drain, rinse under cold water and pat dry.
Dice cooked potato slices.

title: stir-fried chicken salad
directions: Place chicken in a plastic bag set in a deep bowl.
In a small bowl, stir together vinegar, oil, mustard, sugar, salt, paprika and pepper; pour over chicken.
Close bag.
Marinate chicken in refrigerator for 2 to 5 hours, turning bag frequently.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend milk and lime juice.
Then blend in Cool Whip.
Place mixture into pie crust and refrigerate.
Takes about 5 minutes to make.

title: chicken roulades
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in glass casserole dish. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 6 to 7 minutes.
Add bread crumbs and seasonings.
Spread stuffing on chicken and roll up. Hold ends closed with toothpicks.
Arrange in dish; pour combined wine and soup over chicken.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 11 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Overlap 1/8-inch slices of dough roll on 14-inch pizza pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spread over cooled cookie shell. Arrange fruit on top and drizzle with mixture of preserves and water. Chill and serve.

title: hamburger balls and gravy
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper and add onion.
Form into egg size balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons of oil in a deep skillet or small Dutch oven; set aside.
In drippings, mix in and brown flour.
Add water to make a creamy gravy.
Place balls in gravy and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp-macaroni salad
directions: Cut up shrimp; toss with macaroni that has been cooked and cooled.
Add cheese, celery, green peppers and onions.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, stir salad.
May be served in lettuce lined bowl and topped with green pepper rings.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
A favorite of my family.

title: belgium chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter and sugars and beat on a medium speed of electric mixer until soft and well incorporated. Add vanilla.
Add eggs.
Add 1 cup flour.
Mix together salt, cinnamon, baking soda and remaining 2 cups flour and add to batter. Add chips and nuts and mix until incorporated.
Using a spoon or a portion scoop, scoop out batter and roll into balls 1 to 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place on baking sheet and press down slightly to flatten so each looks like a small hockey puck, about 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Bake 10 minutes, no longer; they continue to cook once you pull them out of the oven.

title: peach bavarian jello
directions: Drain peaches; reserve 1/3 cup syrup.
Chop peaches.
Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add syrup.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend almond extract into Cool Whip; gradually blend into jello, then fold in peaches.
Pour into a 5-cup mold.
Chill about 4 hours.

title: wheat-ranch brownies
directions: Melt the chocolate together with the shortening; beat eggs, and sugar gradually, then add flour sifted with salt.
Next add chocolate-shortening mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into two greased shallow pans, 9x13-inch.
Bake in a hot oven 450° about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
May be dusted with powdered sugar while warm.

title: blueberry crumb coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
For base, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
In a separate large bowl, cream softened butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Place blueberries in a bowl and dust with a small amount of flour (this will prevent them from sinking to the bottom!).
Toss to coat.
Add remaining flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture, mixing continually.
Gently fold blueberries into batter.

title: hot sausage and mushroom dip
directions: Heat oil in a 12-inch skillet, cook mushrooms, onion and pepper until tender. Stir in cream cheese and worcestershire. Stir into vegetable mixture. Add sausage. Heat and stir until cheese is melted. Put in a chafing dish. Serve with crackers or corn chips. Makes 4 cups.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a quart jar and shake.

title: angela's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: fish casserole
directions: Place fish in casserole dish.
Cut in half to fit better if needed.
(Fish can be thawed first if desired.)
Mix soup, water and thyme.
Pour over fish.
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 hour or until fish is done.

title: oreo delight
directions: Mix well with a spoon.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover well and freeze.

title: snack pizzas
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat each biscuit into 4-inch circle. Mix tomato sauce and oregano.
Spoon some on each biscuit.
Spoon on meat and mushrooms.
Bake until crust is light brown in 400° oven.
Take out of oven.
Spoon cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken breast fillets in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Stir in sauce, onion, mushrooms and green pepper.
Cover dish; bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove dish from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Place back in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: palm cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: nacho supreme
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch glass casserole dish sprayed with Pam, layer ingredients in order listed.
Cook on High in microwave for 7 to 10 minutes, rotating halfway once or in conventional oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with salad and chips.
Exchanges: 3 1/2 meat; 1 bread; 1/2 vegetable and 1 3/4 fat (with beef) (1 fat with turkey).

title: cubed steak with gravy
directions: Brown steak in oil; add sliced onion rings.
Remove steak from pan.
Add flour, salt and pepper to oil.
Brown flour.
Add water and replace steak; simmer for 30 minutes.
Steak will be very tender.
Great over homemade biscuits.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown onions, celery and peppers in butter. Add tomatoes and simmer at least 1/2 hour. Add peeled and deveined shrimp. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Salt and pepper. Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: smugullian
directions: Brown the beef with diced onion, green pepper, minced garlic and tomatoes.
Add cooked spaghetti (not too done).
You should have approximately 2/3 meat mixture and 1/3 spaghetti.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Very darkly brown finely chopped onion and garlic in olive oil. Remove onion and garlic and dispose. In oil, brown sausage (skinned and mashed) and hamburger with parsley, basil, oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomatoes, sauce, wine, bay leaves and sugar to taste. Carrot and pork chop may be added. Simmer for 4 to 6 hours. Remove carrot and bay leaves.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti. Serves 6 to 8.

title: summer melon salad
directions: Combine chicken, orange sections, grapes, cantaloupe balls, almonds, and mayonnaise.
Chill.
Arrange cantaloupe rings on lettuce and fill with chicken salad.
Garnish with mint or watercress.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Just layer ingredients in a pan.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter (tap sides of pan to distribute crumbs).
Sprinkle on coconut, chocolate morsels and pecans.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over top.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan. Cut in bars.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Beat together with electric mixer all ingredients except shrimp until smooth.
Add shrimp and beat until shrimp is blended and chopped fine.
Serve on crackers or bagels.

title: porkie pine balls
directions: In large bowl mix all ingredients.
Mix and make into balls. Put in large pan and cover with tomato puree.
Cook 1 hour at medium heat.

title: watercress pork
directions: Heat
pan
with oil.
Brown ginger and garlic slightly. Add pork;
fry	for
1	minute.
Put in salt and aji; fry for another minute over a low flame.
Add water.
When it comes to a boil, add watercress.
Cook for 3 minutes, or until done.

title: cranberry squares
directions: Can serve this at Thanksgiving.
It goes great with ham or turkey.

title: armenian lamb stew
directions: Brown lamb in butter.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Saute briefly until onion wilts.
Break up tomatoes and add with oregano to meat.
Simmer until done, about 30 to 45 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add other ingredients and simmer one hour.
During last 20 minutes, add the tortillas which have been cut into 1-inch strips.
Remove pot from burner and add the cheese.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna as directed on package.
Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms to hamburger.
Use 9 x 13-inch loaf pan and place in layers (3 layers) the lasagna, sauce, dab on cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower vegetable casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and mixed vegetables according to directions. Stir Cheddar cheese into white sauce.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer vegetables, onion and pimento.
Pour sauce over and sprinkle cracker crumbs over sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
During last 5 minutes, add onion rings to top of casserole.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar in bowl; blend in oleo until a soft dough is formed.
If dough is too soft to handle, cover and chill.
Shape into 1/4-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: special occasion strawberries
directions: Air dry 3 cups fresh berries.
Combine sugar, cream cheese, juice and rind.
Mix until smooth.
Dip each berry into glaze. Set aside to dry if serving same day.
Refrigerate, if serving later.
Tops may be left on berries for dipping and decorative purposes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: In small bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
In big bowl, mix next 2 ingredients.
Combine small and big bowls.
Crunch up Oreos (scrape off icing).
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save handful of Oreos for top of dessert.
Chill.

title: molded cabbage slaw
directions: In medium mixing bowl, dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice; mix well.
Chill until thickened, but not set, about 30 minutes.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into greased mold or 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm (2 hours).
Serve on lettuce leaves with salad dressing or mayonnaise, if desired.

title: christmas punch for a bunch
directions: Combine the sugar with 1 gallon of the apple juice.
Place over medium heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water for 3 minutes; do not drain.
Cream together the shortening, sugar, liquid sweetener, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour with soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon and blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine flour and baking soda in a small bowl. Beat margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs. Add dry flour mix. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop on cookie sheet (dry); do not grease. Bake for 6 minutes for soft cookies. Clean up fast while cookies cool. Do not leave kitchen sink full of dishes or you will not get to make another batch any time soon.

title: ice cream pie
directions: You will need 1 large spoon, mixer and large bowl.

title: egg rolls
directions: Chop all vegetables fine.
Cover bottom of pan with oil, ham, shrimp, then chicken, salt, pepper, mushrooms, green onion, celery, water chestnuts and bamboo.
Stir after each addition.
Add pepper and 2 tablespoons shoyu.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons Mochiko; stir. Add bean sprouts and watercress; toss.
Place back on platter. Spread out so as not to cook the bean sprouts any more.
Spoon mix on egg roll skin.
Wrap and dab the end with water; fry in deep oil.
Makes 18 egg rolls.

title: faye's cornbread
directions: Mix together well; bake in a 12-inch skillet at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: baked cornbread
directions: Mix meal, flour (plain), salt, sugar, milk, water and egg together.
Use ovensafe pie dish or iron frypan.
Place butter into dish or pan and allow it to melt in oven at 425°.
When butter has melted, pour cornbread mixture into pan.
Place back into oven set at 425° and allow to bake for 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: coconut candy bar cake
directions: Microwave chocolate squares and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, with electric mixer on low speed until completely mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in 1/3 cup of the flour, baking soda and salt. Beat in remaining flour alternately with water until well blended and smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan or wire rack.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup blueberries with 1 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar. Boil for 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt, add to cooked mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add lemon juice and cool.
Put rest of blueberries in cooled pie crust.
Pour glaze over top, then top with Cool Whip.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine first five ingredients in sauce pan. Baste with pastry brush about 15 hamburger buns-both sides. Place ham on basted bun and put Swiss cheese on top. Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes. These sandwiches can be made ahead and placed in freezer until you want to use them. Wrap in foil and just place in oven, as you want them.

title: tomato soup salad(cheese ring)
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Heat soup in boiler.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese. Beat with mixer until thick.
Fold in juice, mayonnaise and vegetables.
Lightly oil mold.
Chill 4 to 5 hours or overnight. Shrimp, olives or crab meat may be added, drained.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: bundt coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil, vanilla, butter flavoring, water and eggs in large mixer bowl.
Beat at high speed of mixer for 8 minutes.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup pecans with the sugar and cinnamon.
Pour a thin layer of cake batter over the pecans in the pan.
Sprinkle some of nut mixture over batter. Alternate batter and nut mixture, ending with batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack for 8 minutes.
Remove from pan and pour glaze over cake.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck with onion and green pepper and make into small balls.
Fry meatballs in skillet until done.
In a large skillet, mix chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil and add meatballs.
Delicious served with butter and garlic noodles.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add margarine and vinegar, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: nutty cherry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 3 Tbsp juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Mix well and spoon into a one quart baking dish.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling water 2 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Serves 7. One half cup serving equals 126 calories.
Exchange is 1 vegetable and 2 fats.

title: lynn's spaghetti
directions: Cook all the seasonings for 25 minutes. Cook noodles last.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add frozen strawberries, pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Set out a few minutes before serving.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Blend well in blender. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: layered skillet meal
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Spread cabbage evenly over margarine.
Sprinkle cabbage with chopped onion.
Arrange potatoes in skillet.
Crumble beef in small pieces and place evenly over potatoes.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover skillet.
Cook over low heat 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and meat is cooked.
Serves 4.
Works good to use leftover spaghetti sauce in place of meat and tomato sauce.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Pare cucumbers and cut lengthwise in very thick slices; wipe them dry with a cloth.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and dredge with flour.
Fry in pan greased with about a tablespoon each of oil and butter.
Brown both sides and serve warm.

title: sweet-and-sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice; set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 3/4 cup.

Add cornstarch, soy sauce, honey, bouillon, garlic and pepper; set aside. Heat oil in a large skillet; cook and stir pork and green peppers for 6 to 8 minutes. Stir pineapple mixture into skillet with pineapple.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Serve over hot rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: homemade bean soup
directions: Rinse beans thoroughly.
Put beans in a large cooking pan. Cover with water, about 3/4 to the top of the pan. Add carrots, celery, onion and ham. Cook on medium heat about 1 1/2 hours.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour longer or until beans are done.
You can cook with lid on or off pan.
You may need to add more water while cooking.
Add more water to make as thin as you want the juice to be.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well with hand mixer.
Chill and serve with Fritos or Bugles.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: helen's pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° to 350° until brown.

title: graham cracker vanilla bars
directions: In 9 X 13 pan (Do not grease or spray) Layer whole graham cracker to coat bottom.
Mix 1/2 cup canned milk, 1 stick margarine, 1/2 cup white sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 egg (slightly beaten).
Mix all together and cook 2 minutes, after bringing to boil.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 cup coconut, 1 cup chopped pecan pieces and 3/4 cup crushed graham cracker.
Cool and spread on top of graham crackers.
Then put another layer of whole graham crackers and ice with Betty Crocker cream cheese icing. Refrigerate.
Cut into bars when ready to serve.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out between wax paper.
Place in pan.
Prick bottom and sides thoroughly with fork.
Bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix
cocoa
and sugar, then add water and salt.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pour into jar and refrigerate.

title: annie's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and cool.
Place layer of macaroni in casserole dish.
Add a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Combine milk and egg; pour over macaroni and cheese.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: dessert dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream until well blended. Refrigerate. Serve with cut up fruit.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Blend in sugar, milk and extract. Fold in whipped topping.
Makes about 4 cups.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: mexican beans
directions: Put all ingredients into a casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: shirley's fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with crackers.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, in hot oil, brown meat on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup and 1 cup of the water. Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables; cook until tender.
Remove meat and vegetables.

title: oatmeal nut bread
directions: Heat milk, water, honey and salt until warm.
Put in bowl; add rest of ingredients and mix.
Roll and knead on floured board. Place in loaf pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil in electric mixer.
Beat at high speed for a minute.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each for one minute. Mix dry ingredients and chopped dates.
Add these to mixture. Fold in vanilla, apples and nuts.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test with straw.

title: layer salad
directions: Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Butter the foil; set pan aside.
Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In the saucepan, combine sugar, milk, peanut butter and corn syrup.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon to dissolve sugar. This should take about 5 minutes.
Avoid splashing mixture on sides of pan.
Carefully clip candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, until thermometer registers 234°, soft ball stage.
Mixture should boil at a moderate, steady rate over the entire surface.
Reaching soft ball stage should take 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry fruit dip
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together all ingredients. Serve with fruit. The dip can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. Serves 8 (2 tablespoons per serving).

title: orange bundt cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add flour, buttermilk and soda alternately; mix well.
Add dates, orange rind and pecans.
Place in Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 250° and bake for about 1 hour or until done.

title: fontbonne bread
directions: Mix well with mixer, gradually adding flour.
Turn onto lightly floured table and knead well.
Let rise until double in size.
Divide dough into two.
Spread melted butter on a baking sheet; sprinkle with cornmeal (amount of butter and cornmeal depending on pans).
Place dough, shaped loaves or rolls on sheet and allow to rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
If desired, can brush with butter or sesame seed.

title: hawaiian pineapple poke cake
directions: Bake cake; poke holes with wooden spoon handle.
Pour crushed pineapple over cake.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese until smooth; spread on top of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: country style rigatoni
directions: Bring water to boil for rigatoni.
Meanwhile, in large saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender.
Add ham, mushrooms and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasoinally, about 2 minutes.
Add wine, parsley and marjoram leaves to ham mixture.
Cover and simmer over low heat.
Add rigatoni, broccoli and potatoes to boiling water. Cook rigatoni to desired doneness as directed on package.
