Drain rigatoni and vegetables.
Rinse with hot water.
In large serving bowl, combine ham mixture, rigatoni and vegetables.
Stir in cheese. Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: nachos casserole
directions: Combine taco sauce and chiles.	Set aside.

title: corn salad
directions: Toss all together and set overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix the flour, oleo and nuts together until crumbly.
Press into a 9
x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: aunt myrna's chicken
directions: Mix together in bowl the preserves, dressing and soup mix. pour mixture over chicken and bake in a 275° to 300° oven for an hour or until crispy.
Enjoy!

title: spanish noodles
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Layer on top the egg noodles (uncooked).
Layer on top of egg noodles the tomatoes, spacing out evenly.
Pour tomato sauce over all, slowly, being sure to wet egg noodles.
Add to wet noodles sufficient water. However, do not add so much that the liquid level rises above the noodles.
Cover; simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine margarine, salt, cheese, egg, milk and onion.
Blend with rice.
Add broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle some cheese on top before serving.

title: cheese-tuna-noodle-scallop
directions: Add 4 teaspoons salt and noodles to 1 1/2 quarts boiling water.
Boil rapidly, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Cover. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: rolled dumplings
directions: Sift flour and salt together. Mix shortening in flour mixture. Add about 3/4 cup milk and mix. Roll thin. Cut in strips. Store in refrigerator for about 2 hours. Drop in boiling broth, either chicken or turkey. Cook for 6 or 7 minutes without stirring.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into a tube pan; let set up, then turn out and slice.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine together until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Mix in mashed bananas and vanilla.

title: layered pretzel jello dessert
directions: Stir together pretzels, 3 Tbsp.
sugar and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Let cool completely.
Mix together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Blend well.
Fold in 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled pretzel layer. Dissolve Jello in hot water then add cold water.
Mix in frozen strawberries and put in freezer for 5 - 7 minutes.
Do not let it jell.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Serve with remainder of Cool Whip. Serves 10 - 12.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: First cream together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Put batter in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and butter.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Pour in 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Serves 16.

title: chunky fruit salad
directions: Mix the instant pudding with the Tang powder.
Add 2 cups fruit juice; stir until dissolved.
Mix in fruit.
Put into covered container; refrigerate overnight.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, celery, green peas, bacon, green pepper, green onions and eggs in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Then mix together the 2 cups of mayonnaise and the 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Pour the mayonnaise and sugar mixture over the other mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: graham coconut chip bars
directions: Combine chips, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix in milk, butter, vanilla and salt.
Spread in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan crunchies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs, flour, soda and pecans; stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion and salt; mix well.
Form into walnut sized balls.
Place in a deep baking dish.
Combine tomato soup, water and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meat balls. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: fabulous cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 2 layers.
Mix and chill 2 cups sugar, sour cream and coconut.
(Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for icing.) Slice the cake layers into 4 layers.
Put coconut mixture between layers.
Add reserved mixture to 1 small carton of Cool Whip.
Ice top and sides of cake.
Put into airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days.
Fabulous!!!

title: mock ravioli
directions: Brown ground round and onion; add spaghetti sauce.
Cook, drain and cool spinach.
To spinach, add bread crumbs, oil, cheese and eggs; mix well.
Place in layers in buttered casserole:
meat sauce, macaroni and spinach.
Repeat; top with sauce and more cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all together. Can put crushed or chopped walnuts on top. Refrigerate.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cook wings in oil. Deep fry 20 to 25 minutes.
Place in pot with hot sauce. Cover tightly and shake to completely cover and soak chicken.

title: pork roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper in roasting pan, fatty side up.
Roast for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Combine Port wine and brown sugar in pan and bring to boil over medium heat.
Cook well.
Thicken and reduce to 1/3 cup (approximately 5 minutes).
Brush pork with this glaze.
Roast meat 1 hour longer basting approximately every 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven, let stand 10 minutes.
Pour juice in gravy ladle to put over meat or rice.
Slice pork with electric knife.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, chicken broth, and water in a large pot.
Bring to a boil, cover, and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes. Stir in soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with diced ham, crumbled bacon, or shredded cheese.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs lightly with wire whisk.
Add corn, sour cream, peppers, cheese, cornmeal and soda.
Mix all ingredients.
Add 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Pour in 10-inch iron skillet; melt 3 tablespoons butter.
While pan is still hot, add batter and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan; add meat, breaking into small pieces with fork.
Add onion and garlic.
When meat is brown, stir in mushrooms with liquid and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until sauce is thickened, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candy's old fashion banana pudding
directions: About 1 hour ahead, separate egg whites from yolk, set aside.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape cookie dough into a ball in center of large pizza pan (round stone).
Using lightly floured roller, roll out dough to 12-inch circle, about 1/4-inch thick. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edge is set.
(Cookie will be soft.
Do not overbake.)
Cool 10 minutes.
Carefully loosen cookie from pan and cool completely.
In small bowl, mix cream cheese and sugar until well blended; set aside.
Pour half and half into large bowl; add pudding mix and whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes until thickened.
Combine cream cheese mixture with pudding mixture until well blended.
Spread pudding mixture over cooled cookie.
Refrigerate for about an hour.
Combine cleaned strawberries and strawberry glaze in large bowl and refrigerate.
Spoon over the top of the pudding and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add crushed potato chips on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: mini chocolate chip cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Line mini muffin tins with paper.
Stir together crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press into paper cups. Melt one cup of mini chips.
In large bowl beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in milk and melted chips.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Spoon into cups and sprinkle with remaining chips.
Bake for 15 minutes.
They freeze great.

title: crescent dinner rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add 1 tablespoon sugar; let stand for 5 minutes. Add the milk, eggs, butter, salt and remaining sugar. Stir in enough flour to form a stiff dough. Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6-8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch dough down. Divide into thirds. Roll each into a 12-in. circle; cut each circle into eight wedges. Brush with melted butter; roll up wedges from the wide end and place, pointed end down, 2 in. apart on greased baking sheets. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pans to wire racks. Makes 2 doz.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. In a large bowl, beat together the eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla until well blended.
Beat in dry ingredients until smooth. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes, or until done. Cool in pan.

title: rice, broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Put rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice margarine and randomly drop over rice.
Dump in remainder of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Stir.
Halves well; freezes well.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream and oil into a batter and pour 1/2 into a 9 x 13 pan. Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts together with a fork. Sprinkle over batter in pan. Pour remaining batter over nut mixture and spread with a knife. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: famous strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and jello.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pour berries in crust.
When mixture cools, pour over berries and refrigerate.
Garnish with Cool Whip when serving.

title: hope's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain. Combine all ingredients. Top with crackers mixed with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust:
Press crescent roll dough into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake according to temperature and time on package.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with the Crumb Topping and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut beef cubes in half; coat with flour and brown in oil in pan.
Add onion and garlic; saute.
Drain and transfer to stock pot.
Add water, bouillon cubes, celery, potatoes and carrots or rutabagas.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add green beans.
Simmer another hour.
Thicken with flour and water, if necessary, before serving. Serve with soft rolls.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins in 6 cups water until a cup of juice is left. Add water if 2 cups is not left.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in large, rectangular pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Cut up bacon; cook until crisp.
Add chopped onion and mushrooms; cook until tender.
Cover with eggs.
Cook until set, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese just long enough until melted.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high about 6 hours.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast on a large piece of aluminum foil.
Pour soup mix and mushroom soup (undiluted) on the roast.
Bring the ends of foil together tightly so juice cannot escape. Cook in a 325° oven for 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into flat casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crackers (crumbled).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until toothpick or knife put into center of cake comes out clean.

title: dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and lemon juice.
Stir until thawed.
Chill until partially set.
Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar, vanilla and salt.
Fold in small amount whipped cream.
Fold in remainder. (May be tinted green for holidays.)
Place cheese mixture on graham cracker crust, 9-inch.
Spoon gelatin mixture on top and refrigerate.

title: refreshing rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and toss.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together apples, sugar and cinnamon. Set aside for 30 minutes.

title: peach cream cheese delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Press into oblong pan or Pyrex, 9 x 13-inches.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown.
Cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook and crumble bacon.
Toss all ingredients together and chill.

title: salmon dill mousse
directions: Combine 1 can salmon (drained and flaked), onion, green pepper, dill and celery.
Set aside.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and the lemon juice. When cool and beginning to jell, add mayonnaise mixed with salmon juice.
Whip this mixture until fluffy.
Fold in salmon mixture. Pour into 1-quart mold until firm.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: microwave meat and potato pie
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, milk, salt and pepper.
Add beef and mix well.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch glass pie plate. Cook on HIGH for 3 minutes.
Combine onion, chili sauce and mustard.
Pour over potatoes and toss lightly.
Spoon into baked meat shell.
Cook on HIGH for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 4 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef
and drain.
Spoon into 8-inch baking dish. Top with
pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Beat
until
smooth
and
pour over casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with raw vegetables. Note:
Light mayonnaise can be substituted for real mayonnaise.

title: corn and tomato casserole
directions: Cut corn from cob; combine corn, onion and green pepper. Saute in 2 tablespoons butter 5 minutes.
Spoon half of corn mixture into 2-quart casserole; top with half of tomato slices. Sprinkle with half of salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Combine bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle evenly over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: piscatella's chicken divan
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken and vegetables, until well incorporated.
Add chicken breast and broccoli to mixture.
Place in covered dish and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Top with bread crumbs and serve.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients together except coconut and nuts.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Put into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef
and	onions	together.
Add	cottage cheese and set aside.
Boil
noodles
in boiling water.
Drain and layer in	baking	dish, sauce, lasagna noodles, Mozzarella cheese; continue until all is used up.
Bake about 25 minutes or until heated thoroughly at 375°, uncovered.

title: mushroom pate
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine in skillet over medium heat until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Put all ingredients in food processor and mix until smooth.
Spoon mixture into greased 7 1/2 x 3 x 3-inch loaf pan. Chill.
Unmold.
Serve with Melba toast or baguette slices.

title: south of the border salad
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Stir in flour, tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, chile peppers and chili powder.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Meanwhile, in salad bowl, combine lettuce, beans and olives and toss.
Place mixture on 6 individual salad plates.
Top lettuce with meat mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Top each salad with a few tomato halves and green pepper strips or a green pepper ring.
Arrange an avocado slice atop each salad.

title: blitz torte
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream the shortening with 1/2 cup of sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, vanilla and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Spread batter into 2 greased cake pans.

title: pumpkin mousse
directions: Mix milk and pudding according to package directions.
Stir in pumpkin and spice.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into dessert dishes and garnish with sprinkle of spice or cinnamon.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: heart smart corn bread
directions: Mix and bake like regular corn bread.
Spray baking pan with Pam.

title: flat apple pie
directions: Mix pastry.
Add egg yolk and milk mixture.
Toss lightly. Divide dough into half.
Roll 1/2 dough to fit a rimmed cookie sheet with edges.
Sprinkle with 2/3 cup crushed cornflakes over dough.

title: dirty rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread rice in loaf pan.
Add margarine and soup; do not stir.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: congo squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar. Cool.
Add eggs to sugar mixture.
Beat.
Add salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Put in a 350° oven for 1 minute.
Remove from oven and swirl chips with knife.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Note:
Chop cherries, pineapple and pecans fine.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain well. Cut up Velveeta into cubes.
Mix broccoli and cheese well in pan until cheese is melted (on low heat).
Pour into casserole dish. Put a thin layer of cracker crumbs over entire casserole.
Mix lemon juice and melted butter.
Pour evenly over crackers.
Allow a few minutes for the butter to be absorbed.
Bake until topping turns light brown or crusty (approximately 15 minutes).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sopaipillas(fried bread)
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Cut in fat and add water to hold together.
Roll dough thin and cut into small squares.
Fry in deep, hot lard about 400°.
This bread will puff like a little pillow.
Fill with honey or roll in cinnamon and sugar or powdered sugar.
A nice dessert.

title: cheesy tators
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1/4-inch thick slices, onion also. Cook. Butter glass dish. Put half potatoes in dish. Cover with cheese and pats of butter. Put other half of potatoes in. Cover with cheese and butter. Pour in milk. Melt cheese. Serve warm.

title: party punch
directions: Combine Punch and lemonade; just before serving, add Sprite or Seven-Up.
Serve over ice.
Makes approximately 30 servings.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Heat oil at medium-high heat in 12-inch saute pan or wok for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables, tossing and stirring gently for about 5 minutes.
Vegetables should be crisp and tender.
Add soy sauce and salt; toss to mix.
Sprinkle sesame seed over top (optional). Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness. Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in egg. Coat with bread crumbs. Place chicken on a baking sheet. Cool and chill for 10 minutes. Saute chicken in olive oil over medium-low heat 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Remove chicken from skillet. Place in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon spaghetti sauce on chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Top with Parmesan cheese and bake an additional minutes or until cheese melts and sauce is bubbly.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter and set aside.
In same pan add 4 tablespoons butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until sauce is bubbly.
Add milk; cook and stir until sauce boils for one minute.
Add wine (I like dry vermouth best), chicken, spaghetti and mushrooms.
Spoon into lightly greased 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° until hot through and crumbs are toasted golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix well. Place in small containers and place in freezer.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix milk and
lemon
juice; add Cool Whip and mix.
Add chopped oranges and
nuts.	Pour into graham cracker crust and chill until firm.

title: genoese cake
directions: In a large pan, preferably copper, mix sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla bean.
Over very low heat, gently beat the ingredients with a whisk.
This process can be done in a double boiler.
When the mixture begins to foam and rise well up in pan, remove from heat and continue whisking until the mixture is cold.
Remove vanilla bean.
Continue beating, gradually adding flour via a sifter. Whisk in softened butter.

title: safari cookies
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Beat together butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Resift flour with salt, cinnamon and soda.
Blend into butter mixture.
Mix in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until browned.
Remove to racks to cool.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine water, butter and cocoa in sauce pan and bring to boil. Combine sugar and flour in large bowl. Pour hot cocoa mixture over sugar and flour. Add eggs, baking soda, milk and salt. Blend well. Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet. Add nuts if desired.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain liquid from the asparagus and the mushrooms and place in a boiler.
Add enough butter, milk and flour to this liquid to make a white sauce.
Add garlic that has been put through a garlic press to the white sauce.
Place the asparagus in a casserole. Add mushrooms, eggs, cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Pour sauce on it and stir.
Cover the top with cracker crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: five-hour beef stew
directions: Bake at 250° for 5 hours in iron skillet or Dutch oven.
Cover dish.

title: mexico dinner
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix in all other ingredients with meat in skillet.
(If you wish to use Minute rice instead, put it in dry and it will cook with the sauce.)

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix the cream cheese and mayonnaise, then squeeze the half of lemon twice into the bowl.
Dice cucumber to desired size into the mixture.
Stir and spread on your favorite bread.

title: cinnamon red hot pickles
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers.
Slice 1/4-inch thick or cut in strips.
Soak in 1 cup lime and 1 gallon water for 24 hours.
Wash. Soak in ice water for 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, food coloring and alum with enough water to cover.
Pour over cucumbers and simmer for 2 hours.
Pour off.	Bring to boil 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, cinnamon sticks and Red Hot candy.
Boil until candy is melted.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours. After 24 hours, pour the liquid into a boiler and bring to a boil. Pack cucumbers into jars.
Pour hot mixture over and seal.

title: quick picante sauce dip
directions: Whip cream cheese and spread onto pie plate.
Pour picante sauce over it; dip in chips.

title: picadillo (filling for tacos)
directions: Cook ground beef until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onion, garlic and peppers.
Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve as a filling in corn or flour tortillas that have been warmed on a grill or in the microwave.
Serve with hot sauce.
Especially good with frijoles (beans).

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place condensed milk and eggs into bowl and mix until smooth. Add lemon juice and zest and stir until incorporated. Pour milk mixture into crust. Bake pie for 15 minutes. Cool completely and freeze. Serve chilled for best results. Can be baked and frozen for 2 weeks before serving.

title: fruit turnovers
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening and mix.
Add all milk and eggs.
Roll very thin in circle, about 6 inches in diameter.
Put any kind of fruit on dough.
Wet edges of dough and fold over; crimp with fork.
Cook in hot, deep fat. Makes about 30 pies.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add to beaten eggs, butter, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in unbaked pie shells on a cookie sheet for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pickle relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, onions and peppers and let stand in colander 1 hour.
Cook all other ingredients together for 20 minutes.
Then mix with cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Put in jars.
Cold pack for 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, oil, flavoring, egg and sugar. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine ingredients together. Drop by teaspoon and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1 stick butter, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over crumbs.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Top with pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with pecans and cherries. (Let set 12 hours before serving.)

title: saucy skillet potatoes
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine over low heat.
Add onions; cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, cook stirring constantly, 2 minutes or until hot.
(Do not boil!) Sprinkle with parsley and bacon.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break up cake in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Make jello (leaving out 1 cup cold water).
Stir in thawed strawberries.
Pour on cake and place in refrigerator until cake absorbs the jello.
Make pudding in refrigerator until cool, then top the cake.
Now top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated and covered.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Spray Dutch oven with cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion, chiles and garlic; cook until onion is tender.
Add water, tomato juice, tomato, bouillon cube, cumin, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and hot sauce; stir well.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add tortillas, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle soup into bowls, sprinkle 1 tablespoon cheese over each.
Garnish with cilantro sprig.
Contains 89 calories per cup.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put margarine in a square baking pan and melt while heating oven.
Put all other ingredients, except cinnamon sugar, into a bowl.
Mix with a wire whisk or mixer.
Pour into baking pan with melted margarine.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until they form soft peaks.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until smooth and glossy. Add syrup, a little at a time and beat after each addition until frosting holds firm peaks.
Fold in vanilla.

title: busy day oven stew
directions: Place meat in 2-quart casserole.
Add vegetables and sprinkle salt, flour and soy sauce over all.
Pour tomatoes on top and cover.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: good friday pancakes
directions: Mix together and beat hard.
Heat a skillet at about medium heat.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Pour batter into skillet.
Make whatever size.
Cover with lid.
When bottom side is done, flip.
Makes 4 to 8 pancakes, depends on size.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs as usual.
Allow potatoes to cool, then peel and cut into small pieces.
Add chopped eggs.
Mix in a bowl with the celery, onions, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package; drain and rinse with cold water.
Set aside.
Combine lettuce, onion, ham, Cheddar cheese, pickles, green peppers, radishes, celery and carrots.
Mix well. Stir in spaghetti, then combine mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over spaghetti and toss to coat. Serve on lettuce if desired.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; spread on pie pan.
Pour chili sauce over cream cheese mixture.
Mix together remaining ingredients and put on top.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts; drain and set aside when done.
Mix together mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup and lemon juice.
In casserole dish, layer broccoli spears (thawed) and cooked chicken breasts.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top of casserole.
Layer butter over the topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in bread pan for 1 hour, or until done, at 350°.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish, fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for another 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut up, fry and drain the bacon.
Brown ground beef with the onion.
Drain three cans of beans.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Heat cream over medium low heat
in a deep saute pan. Add butter and whisk gently to melt. Stir in cheese. Season with pepper.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together butter, soup, cheese, sour cream and onion.
Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle melted butter over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts stuffed with spinach(6 servings)
directions: Thaw spinach; drain and squeeze real dry.
Chop green onions into spinach mixture; stir this mixture into softened cream cheese.
Saute sliced mushrooms in butter until all moisture has evaporated and mushrooms have softened.
Pour this mushroom mixture into spinach-onion/cream mixture; stir until well mixed. This is your stuffing.

title: apple cranberry bake
directions: Butter a 9-inch casserole dish.
Cut up apples in bottom. Sprinkle 1/3 cup sugar over apples.
Spread cranberry sauce over sugar.
Melt the butter.
Add oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Put this on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quiche
directions: Coat pan with butter.
Put vegetables on bottom.
Grate cheese and put over vegetables.
Mix milk, flour and eggs.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown.
Let cool for 15 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat brown sugar, vinegar, water, salt, pepper and caraway seeds in bacon drippings.
Add cabbage and apples stirring to coat.
Add crumbled bacon.
Cover and cook over medium low heat, stirring occasionally.
For crisper cabbage, cook 15 minutes.
For tender cabbage cook 30 minutes.

title: cran-raspberry mold
directions: In bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and cranberry sauce, stirring until cranberry sauce melts.
Chill until partially set by placing bowl into a larger bowl of ice water, or chill in refrigerator.
Pour half of the gelatin mixture into a 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Chill until almost firm.
Let the remaining jello stand at room temperature.
In small bowl, stir sour cream until smooth; spread evenly over the almost firm jello in mold.
Gently spoon remaining jello on top of the sour cream layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate. Makes 12 servings.

title: ginger apple nut punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, cream of coconut and ginger ale well. Add vanilla ice cream.
Stir slightly and serve.
Good at holidays.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Bring water, potatoes, pepper and bouillon cubes to boil.
Add bag of frozen veggies and bring to a boil.
Add Velveeta cheese and chicken soup.
Add salt to taste.
Simmer.

title: pineapple icebox fluff
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan with crushed wafers.

title: aunt beulah's liver nips
directions: In an 8-cup measuring bowl, microwave 2 1/2 cups water on High for 8 minutes or until boiling.
Add pasta and cook on High 5 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: rainbow chiffon jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 separate bowls using 3/4 cup hot water in each bowl and 3/4 cup of cold water.
Set in refrigerator until very thick.
Beat each bowl of jello.
Add one Cool Whip to each bowl and whip with electric beater until frothy.
Place in layers in Bundt pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Set 3 hours before serving.
Put raspberry on top, lemon in middle and lime on bottom.

title: strawberry orange punch
directions: Combine concentrated orange juice and water in punch bowl. Mix well.
Add ice cubes.
Add ginger ale.
Float strawberries in punch.
Garnish with mint leaves if desired.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix soup and chicken broth.
Add Veg-All.
Put in greased baking dish.
Add eggs and chicken.
For the crust, mix milk, butter and flour.
Pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: leroy's tri-tip bake
directions: Salt and pepper Tri-Tip and barbecue until rare.
When meat cools, slice thin.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Heat all 3 cans of soup in saucepan until smooth.
Pour over sliced meat.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Delicious.

title: mushroom-dill chicken rolls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir cut margarine into hot water in bowl until melted.
Add stuffing crumbs, red pepper and egg; stir until moistened.
Spoon stuffing on chicken and roll tightly.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place in greased pan and bake 45 minutes or until cooked through.
Heat soup, water and dill.
Serve over chicken.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Cook chicken and vegetables until chicken is done, 45 minutes. Bone chicken, but leave in big pieces.
To liquid, add noodles and cook to package directions.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add eggs and milk and mix with beater.
Slowly add coffee and beat until well mixed.
Batter will be very thin.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts on bottom of greased pan. Prepare cake mix as directed; pour over coconut and nuts.
Combine cream cheese, margarine and sugar; stir in vanilla.
Drop last mixture by teaspoonfuls all over top of cake.
(This will just about cover the cake.) Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large bowl, mix 4 cups rice and all six cans of soup.
Pour into a large deep pan or two small ones. Spread evenly.
Place pieces of chicken separately on top of rice. Drizzle melted butter over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue basting solution
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; heat well.
Brush or spray over chicken every 5 to 10 minutes while grilling.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Drain.
Cut broccoli flowerets from stems and pour boiling water over flowerets in a colander.
Drain well.
Combine broccoli, crab meat, carrots, celery, and green pepper in a large bowl and mix well.
Combine oil and vinegar in small bowl.
Add seasonings, mix well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over pasta and chill until serving time.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Brown sausage and vegetables until vegetables are tender.
Mash cooked and drained squash.
Combine all ingredients except for 1 cup of the grated cheese.
Pour into a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with the remaining cheese.
Return to oven for about 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Tear bread and place in greased casserole. Brown sausage and drain.
Sprinkle over bread.
Beat eggs, milk, Cheddar and mustard.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easter egg nests
directions: Mix ingredients in a double boiler until melted.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on wax paper.
Shape into nest shapes.
Let set until cool.
Fill with jelly beans.
Kids love them.

title: aunt nannie's chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chopped green pepper and onion in butter until soft.
Add flour, milk, cream of chicken soup and chicken.
Heat all together.
Pour in baking dish and cover with biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are nicely browned.

title: country ham
directions: Scrub ham in warm water with a stiff brush and rinse.
Place ham in a large stockpot.
Cover with water.
Add vinegar and let stand 24 hours.
Drain ham and rinse, return to stockpot.
Add water to cover and add apple juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 140 degrees.
Add hot water as needed to cover ham.
Remove from heat and let stand 2 hours.
Drain ham, trim skin, leaving a thin layer of fat.
Stir together bread crumbs, brown sugar and pepper, press over ham.
Cool completely. Cut ham into thin slices, reserving any breadcrumbs mixture that detaches.
Serve ham and breadcrumbs mixture in biscuits.
Yield: 30 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk to sugar mixture.
Add prunes, coconut and raisins.
Turn into angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: garlic tomato soup
directions: Heat oil; saute garlic for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove pan from heat; stir in paprika.
Return to low heat; stir 1 minute.
The minute it sizzles, add broth and tomatoes.
Puree in blender, then simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add Tabasco and butter.
Serves 6.
